WEBVTT

00:00:20.700 --> 00:00:25.520
CHAPTER I The vision of Isaiah, the son of Amoz, which

00:00:25.520 --> 00:00:32.880
concerning Judah and Jerusalem in the days of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah kings of Judah.

00:00:33.600 --> 00:00:41.500
Hear, O heavens, and give ear, O earth, for the Lord hath spoken. I have nourished and brought

00:00:41.500 --> 00:00:49.480
up children, and they have rebelled against me. The ox knoweth his owner, and the ass his master's

00:00:49.480 --> 00:00:59.260
crib, but Israel doth not know. My people doth not consider. Ah, sinful nation, a people laden with

00:00:59.260 --> 00:01:06.620
iniquity, a seed of evildoers, children that are corrupters. They have forsaken the Lord,

00:01:06.960 --> 00:01:13.040
they have provoked the Holy One of Israel unto anger. They are gone away backward.

00:01:13.900 --> 00:01:21.500
Why should ye be stricken any more? Ye will revolt more and more. The whole head is sick,

00:01:21.860 --> 00:01:28.860
and the whole heart faint. From the sole of the foot even unto the head there is no soundness in

00:01:28.860 --> 00:01:36.840
it but wounds, and bruises, and putrefying sores. They have not been closed, neither bound up,

00:01:36.840 --> 00:01:43.500
neither mollified with ointment. Your country is desolate, your cities are burned with fire,

00:01:43.800 --> 00:01:51.020
your land strangers devour it in your presence, and it is desolate as overthrown by strangers.

00:01:51.860 --> 00:01:58.440
And the daughter of Zion is left as a cottage in a vineyard, as a lodge in a garden of cucumbers,

00:01:59.320 --> 00:02:05.020
as a besieged city. Except the Lord of Host had left unto us a very small remnant,

00:02:05.020 --> 00:02:09.980
we should have been as Sodom, and we should have been like unto Gomorrah.

00:02:10.100 --> 00:02:16.000
Hear the word of the Lord, ye rulers of Sodom, give ear unto the law of our God, ye people of

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:22.380
Gomorrah. To what purpose is the multitude of your sacrifices unto me, saith the Lord?

00:02:22.620 --> 00:02:29.560
I am full of the burnt offerings of rams, and the fat of fed beasts, and I delight not in the blood

00:02:29.560 --> 00:02:35.980
of bullocks, or of lambs, or of he-goats. When ye come to appear before me, who hath required

00:02:35.980 --> 00:02:45.560
this at your hand to tread my cords? Bring no more vain oblations. Incense is an abomination unto me.

00:02:45.880 --> 00:02:54.000
The new moons and Sabbaths, the calling of assemblies, I cannot away with. It is iniquity,

00:02:54.000 --> 00:03:01.800
even the solemn meeting. Your new moons and your appointed feasts my soul hateth.

00:03:02.260 --> 00:03:08.260
They are a trouble unto me. I am weary to bear them. And when ye spread forth your hands,

00:03:08.340 --> 00:03:16.720
I will hide mine eyes from you. Yea, when ye make many prayers, I will not hear. Your hands are full

00:03:16.720 --> 00:03:25.720
of blood. Wash you. Make you clean. Put away the evil of your doings, from before mine eyes cease

00:03:25.720 --> 00:03:34.040
to do evil. Learn to do well. Seek judgment. Relieve the oppressed. Judge the fatherless.

00:03:34.740 --> 00:03:42.260
Plead for the widow. Come now, let us reason together, saith the Lord. Though your sins be

00:03:42.260 --> 00:03:51.120
scarlet, they shall be as white as snow. Though they be red like crimson, they shall be as wool.

00:03:52.300 --> 00:04:00.360
If ye be willing and obedient, ye shall eat the good of the land. But if ye refuse and rebel,

00:04:01.240 --> 00:04:06.160
ye shall be devoured with the sword, for the mouth of the Lord hath spoken it.

00:04:06.960 --> 00:04:16.060
How is the faithful city becoming harlot? It was full of judgment. Righteousness lodged in it.

00:04:16.820 --> 00:04:25.340
But now murderers. Thy silver is become dross. Thy wine mixed with water. Thy princes are

00:04:25.340 --> 00:04:33.280
rebellious and companions of thieves. Everyone loveth gifts and followeth after rewards. They judge

00:04:33.280 --> 00:04:39.400
not the fatherless, neither doth the cause of the widow come unto them. Therefore saith the Lord,

00:04:39.580 --> 00:04:48.240
the Lord of hosts, the mighty one of Israel, I will ease me of mine adversaries, and avenge me

00:04:48.240 --> 00:04:57.480
of mine enemies. And I will turn my hand upon thee, and purely purge away thy dross, and take away all

00:04:57.480 --> 00:05:05.460
thy men. And I will restore thy judges as at the first, and thy counsellors as at the beginning.

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:13.600
Afterward thou shalt be called the city of righteousness, the faithful city. Zion shall

00:05:13.600 --> 00:05:20.560
be redeemed with judgment, and her converts with righteousness. And the destruction of the transgressors

00:05:20.560 --> 00:05:26.740
and of the sinners shall be together. And they that forsake the Lord shall be consumed.

00:05:27.520 --> 00:05:34.900
For they shall be ashamed of the oaks which ye have desired, and ye shall be confounded for the

00:05:34.900 --> 00:05:43.540
gardens that ye have chosen. For ye shall be as an oak whose leaf fadeth, and as a garden that

00:05:43.540 --> 00:05:52.540
hath no water. And the strong shall be as toe, and the maker of it as a spark. And they shall

00:05:52.540 --> 00:06:01.780
both burn together, and none shall quench them. Chapter 2. The word that Isaiah the son of Amoz

00:06:01.780 --> 00:06:09.480
saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem. And it shall come to pass in the last days, that the mountain

00:06:09.480 --> 00:06:15.640
of the Lord's house shall be established in the top of the mountains, and shall be exalted above

00:06:15.640 --> 00:06:23.860
the hills, and all the nations shall flow unto it. And many people shall go, and say, Come ye,

00:06:24.180 --> 00:06:30.140
and let us go up to the mountain of the Lord, to the house of the God of Jacob. And he will teach

00:06:30.140 --> 00:06:38.460
us of his ways, and we will walk in his paths. For out of Zion shall go forth the law, and the

00:06:38.460 --> 00:06:45.620
word of the Lord from Jerusalem. And he shall judge among the nations, and shall rebuke many people.

00:06:45.640 --> 00:06:53.520
And they shall beat their swords into plowshares, and their spears into pruning-hooks. Nations shall

00:06:53.520 --> 00:07:01.920
not lift up sword against nation, neither shall they learn war any more. O house of Jacob, come ye,

00:07:02.420 --> 00:07:08.780
let us walk in the light of the Lord. Therefore thou hast forsaken thy people the house of Jacob,

00:07:08.780 --> 00:07:14.800
because they be replenished from the east, and are soothsayers like the Philistines,

00:07:15.220 --> 00:07:21.620
and they please themselves in the children of strangers. Their land also is full of silver and

00:07:21.620 --> 00:07:28.340
gold, neither is there any end of their treasures. Their land is also full of horses, neither is there

00:07:28.340 --> 00:07:35.560
any end of their chariots. Their land is also full of idols. They worship the work of their own hands,

00:07:35.560 --> 00:07:42.960
that which their own fingers have made. And the mean man boweth down, and the great man

00:07:42.960 --> 00:07:50.520
humbleth himself. Therefore forgive them not. Enter into the rock, and hide thee in the dust,

00:07:50.880 --> 00:07:57.780
for fear of the Lord, and for the glory of his majesty. The lofty looks of man shall be humbled,

00:07:58.480 --> 00:08:04.980
and the haughtiness of men shall be bowed down, and the Lord alone shall be exalted in that day.

00:08:05.560 --> 00:08:10.920
For the day of the Lord of hosts shall be upon every one that is proud and lofty,

00:08:11.780 --> 00:08:19.980
and upon every one that is lifted up, and he shall be brought low, and upon all the cedars of Lebanon

00:08:19.980 --> 00:08:27.080
that are high and lifted up, and upon all the oaks of Basian, and upon all the high mountains,

00:08:27.520 --> 00:08:34.740
and upon all the hills that are lifted up, and upon every high tower, and upon every fenced wall,

00:08:34.740 --> 00:08:40.580
and upon all the ships of Tarshish, and upon all pleasant pictures.

00:08:42.140 --> 00:08:48.180
And the loftiness of man shall be bowed down, and the haughtiness of men shall be made low,

00:08:49.060 --> 00:08:56.420
and the Lord alone shall be exalted in that day. And the idols he shall utterly abolish,

00:08:57.660 --> 00:09:02.800
and they shall go into the holes of the rocks, and into the caves of the earth,

00:09:02.800 --> 00:09:08.980
for fear of the Lord, and for the glory of his majesty, when he ariseth to shake terribly the

00:09:08.980 --> 00:09:16.860
earth. In that day a man shall cast his idols of silver, and his idols of gold, which they made

00:09:16.860 --> 00:09:24.340
each one for himself to worship, to the moles, and to the bats, to go into the clefts of the rocks,

00:09:24.900 --> 00:09:31.660
and into the tops of the ragged rocks, for fear of the Lord, and for the glory of his majesty,

00:09:31.660 --> 00:09:39.480
when he ariseth to shake terribly the earth. Cease ye from man, whose breath is in his nostrils,

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:47.640
for wherein is he to be accounted of? Chapter 3 For behold, the Lord, the Lord of hosts,

00:09:47.880 --> 00:09:54.300
doth take away from Jerusalem, and from Judah, the stay, and the staff, the whole stay of bread,

00:09:54.580 --> 00:10:00.680
and the whole stay of water, the mighty man, and the man of war, the judge, and the prophet,

00:10:00.680 --> 00:10:06.880
and the prudent, and the ancient, the captain of fifty, and the honorable man, and the counselor,

00:10:07.360 --> 00:10:14.140
and the cunning artificer, and the eloquent orator, and I will give children to be their princes,

00:10:15.020 --> 00:10:21.160
and babes shall rule over them, and the people shall be oppressed every one by another,

00:10:21.540 --> 00:10:27.400
and every one by his neighbor, the child shall behave himself proudly against the ancient,

00:10:27.400 --> 00:10:34.200
and the base against the honorable. When a man shall take hold of his brother of the house of

00:10:34.200 --> 00:10:40.980
his father, saying, Thou hast clothing, be thou our ruler, and let this ruin be under thy hand.

00:10:41.560 --> 00:10:48.200
In that day shall he swear, saying, I will not be in healer, for in my house is neither bread,

00:10:48.320 --> 00:10:56.080
nor clothing, make me not a ruler of the people. For Jerusalem is ruined, and Judah has fallen,

00:10:56.080 --> 00:11:02.300
because their tongue and their doings are against the Lord, to provoke the eyes of his glory.

00:11:03.500 --> 00:11:09.160
The show of their countenance doth witness against them, and they declare their sin as

00:11:09.160 --> 00:11:16.180
sodom they hided not. Woe unto their soul, for they have rewarded evil unto themselves.

00:11:16.920 --> 00:11:22.320
Say ye to the righteous, that it shall be well with him, for they shall eat the fruit of their

00:11:22.320 --> 00:11:30.760
doings. Woe unto the wicked, it shall be ill with him, for the reward of his hands shall be given

00:11:30.760 --> 00:11:39.220
him. As for my people, children are their oppressors, and women rule over them. O my people,

00:11:39.940 --> 00:11:47.620
they which lead thee cause thee to err, and destroy the way of thy paths. The Lord standeth

00:11:47.620 --> 00:11:54.620
up to plead, and standeth to judge the people. The Lord will enter into judgment with the

00:11:54.620 --> 00:12:02.020
ancients of his people, and the princes thereof, for ye have eaten up the vineyard. The spoil of

00:12:02.020 --> 00:12:10.700
the poor is in your houses. What mean ye, that ye beat my people to pieces, and grind the faces

00:12:10.700 --> 00:12:17.600
of the poor, saith the Lord God of hosts? Moreover, the Lord saith, because the daughters of Zion are

00:12:17.600 --> 00:12:24.180
haughty, and walk with stretched forth necks and wanton eyes, walking and mincing as they go,

00:12:24.500 --> 00:12:30.880
and making a tinkling with their feet. Therefore the Lord will smite with a scab the crown of the

00:12:30.880 --> 00:12:38.240
head of the daughters of Zion, and the Lord will discover their secret paths. In that day, the Lord

00:12:38.240 --> 00:12:43.560
will take away the bravery of their tinkling ornaments about their feet, and their calls,

00:12:43.560 --> 00:12:49.080
and their round tires like the moon, the chains, and the bracelets, and the mufflers,

00:12:49.480 --> 00:12:54.740
the bonnets, and the ornaments of the legs, and the headbands, and the tablets, and the earrings,

00:12:55.080 --> 00:13:02.240
the rings, and the nose jewels, the changeable suits of apparel, and the mantles, and the wimples,

00:13:02.580 --> 00:13:10.160
and the crisping pins, the glasses, and the fine linen, and the hoods, and the veils.

00:13:10.160 --> 00:13:15.340
And it shall come to pass, that instead of sweet smell there shall be stink,

00:13:16.580 --> 00:13:23.460
and instead of a girdle a rent, and instead of well-set hair baldness, and instead of a

00:13:23.460 --> 00:13:32.140
stomacher a girding of sackcloth, and burning instead of beauty. Thy men shall fall by the sword,

00:13:32.140 --> 00:13:37.820
and thy mighty in the war, and her gates shall lament and mourn,

00:13:38.380 --> 00:13:42.060
and she being desolate shall sit upon the ground.

00:13:49.420 --> 00:13:50.020
4.

00:14:04.720 --> 00:14:11.480
And in that day seven women shall take hold of one man, saying, We will eat our own bread,

00:14:11.480 --> 00:14:17.880
and wear our own apparel. Only let us be called by thy name, to take away our reproach.

00:14:19.000 --> 00:14:25.780
And in that day shall the branch of the Lord be beautiful and glorious, and the fruit of the earth

00:14:25.780 --> 00:14:32.070
shall be excellent and comely for them that are escaped of Israel. And it shall come to pass,

00:14:32.960 --> 00:14:39.620
that he that is left in Zion, and he that remaineth in Jerusalem, shall be called holy,

00:14:39.620 --> 00:14:45.580
even every one that is written among the living in Jerusalem. When the Lord shall have washed away

00:14:45.580 --> 00:14:51.500
the filth of the daughters of Zion, and shall have purged the blood of Jerusalem from the midst

00:14:51.500 --> 00:14:58.940
thereof, by the spirit of judgment, and by the spirit of burning. And the Lord will create upon

00:14:58.940 --> 00:15:09.600
every dwelling place of Mount Zion, and upon her assemblies a cloud and smoke by day, and the

00:15:09.600 --> 00:15:16.800
glory shall be a defense. And there shall be a tabernacle for a shadow in the daytime from the

00:15:16.800 --> 00:15:24.360
heat, and for a place of refuge, and for a covert from the storm and from rain. 5.

00:15:25.300 --> 00:15:33.280
Now will I sing to my well-beloved a song of my beloved touching his vineyard. My well-beloved

00:15:33.920 --> 00:15:40.620
hath a vineyard in a very fruitful hill. And he fenced it, and gathered out the stones thereof,

00:15:40.780 --> 00:15:47.860
and planted it with the choicest vine, and built a tower in the midst of it, and also made a wine

00:15:47.860 --> 00:15:55.100
press therein. And he looked that it should bring forth grapes, and it brought forth wild grapes.

00:15:55.820 --> 00:16:01.660
And now, O inhabitants of Jerusalem, and men of Judah, judge, I pray you,

00:16:01.880 --> 00:16:08.540
betwixt me and my vineyard, what could have been done more to my vineyard that I have not done in

00:16:08.540 --> 00:16:15.040
it? Wherefore, when I looked that it should bring forth grapes, brought it forth wild grapes?

00:16:15.880 --> 00:16:22.660
And now go, too, I will tell you what I will do to my vineyard. I will take away the hedge thereof,

00:16:22.660 --> 00:16:28.160
and it shall be eaten up, and break down the wall thereof, and it shall be trodden down.

00:16:28.280 --> 00:16:35.500
And I will lay it waste. It shall not be pruned nor digged, but there shall come up briars and

00:16:35.500 --> 00:16:42.680
thorns. I will also command the clouds that they rain no rain upon it. For the vineyard of the

00:16:42.680 --> 00:16:51.060
Lord of hosts is the house of Israel, and the men of Judah his pleasant plant. And he looked for

00:16:51.060 --> 00:17:00.700
judgment but behold oppression, for righteousness but behold a cry. Woe unto them that join house

00:17:00.700 --> 00:17:08.760
to house, that lay field to field, till there be no place, that they may be placed alone in the

00:17:08.760 --> 00:17:17.080
midst of the earth. In mine ears, said the Lord of hosts, of a truth many houses shall be desolate,

00:17:17.080 --> 00:17:24.480
even great and fair without inhabitant. Yea, ten acres of vineyard shall yield one bath,

00:17:25.020 --> 00:17:32.380
and the seed of an homer shall yield an ephah. Woe unto them that rise up early in the morning,

00:17:32.620 --> 00:17:40.220
that they may follow strong drink, that continue until night, till wine inflame them. And the harp,

00:17:40.220 --> 00:17:48.340
and the vial, the tabret, and pipe, and wine are in their feasts. But they regard not the work of

00:17:48.340 --> 00:17:56.860
the Lord, neither consider the operation of his hands. Therefore my people are gone into captivity,

00:17:57.480 --> 00:18:04.100
because they have no knowledge, and their honorable men are famished, and their multitude dried up

00:18:04.100 --> 00:18:10.720
with thirst. Therefore hell hath enlarged herself, and opened her mouth without measure,

00:18:11.400 --> 00:18:19.880
and their glory, and their multitude, and their pomp, and he that rejoiceth shall descend into it.

00:18:20.440 --> 00:18:25.400
And the mean man shall be brought down, and the mighty man shall be humbled,

00:18:26.140 --> 00:18:33.660
and the eyes of the lofty shall be humbled. But the Lord of hosts shall be exalted in judgment,

00:18:34.100 --> 00:18:40.620
and God that is holy shall be sanctified in righteousness. Then shall the lambs feed

00:18:40.620 --> 00:18:48.200
after their manor, and the waste places of the fat ones shall strangers eat. Woe unto them that

00:18:48.200 --> 00:18:56.620
draw iniquity with cords of vanity, and sin as it were with a cart-rope, that say, Let him make speed

00:18:56.620 --> 00:19:03.180
and hasten his work that we may see it, and let the counsel of the Holy One of Israel draw nigh

00:19:03.180 --> 00:19:11.940
and come that we may know it. Woe unto them that call evil good, and good evil, that put darkness

00:19:11.940 --> 00:19:20.160
for light, and light for darkness, that put bitter for sweet, and sweet for bitter. Woe unto them

00:19:20.160 --> 00:19:27.460
that are wise in their own eyes, and prudent in their own sight. Woe unto them that are mighty

00:19:27.460 --> 00:19:35.060
to drink wine, and men of strength to mingle strong drink, which justify the wicked for reward,

00:19:35.520 --> 00:19:43.160
and take away the righteousness of the righteous from him. Therefore, as the fire devoureth the

00:19:43.160 --> 00:19:52.060
stubble, and the flame consumeth the chaff, so their root shall be as rottenness, and their blossom

00:19:52.060 --> 00:19:59.560
shall go up as dust, because they have cast away the law of the Lord of hosts, and despised the

00:19:59.560 --> 00:20:06.140
word of the Holy One of Israel. Therefore is the anger of the Lord kindled against his people,

00:20:06.780 --> 00:20:13.500
and he hath stretched forth his hand against them, and hath smitten them, and the hills did tremble,

00:20:13.700 --> 00:20:21.860
and their carcasses were torn in the midst of the streets. For all this his anger is not turned away,

00:20:22.060 --> 00:20:29.520
but his hand is stretched out still, and he will lift up an ensign to the nations from far,

00:20:30.040 --> 00:20:37.580
and will hiss unto them from the end of the earth, and behold, they shall come with speed swiftly.

00:20:38.840 --> 00:20:45.460
None shall be weary nor stumble among them, none shall slumber nor sleep, neither shall the girdle

00:20:45.460 --> 00:20:52.300
of their loins be loosed, nor the latchet of their shoes be broken, whose arrows are sharp,

00:20:52.860 --> 00:20:58.960
and all their bows bent, their horses' hooves shall be counted like flint, and their wheels

00:20:58.960 --> 00:21:06.820
like a whirlwind. Their roaring shall be like a lion, they shall roar like young lions, yea,

00:21:06.840 --> 00:21:13.840
they shall roar and lay hold of the prey, and shall carry it away safe, and none shall deliver it.

00:21:15.460 --> 00:21:22.940
And in that day they shall roar against them like the roaring of the sea, and if one look unto the

00:21:22.940 --> 00:21:30.360
land, behold, darkness and sorrow, and the light is darkened in the heavens thereof.

00:21:31.380 --> 00:21:38.700
Chapter 6 In the year that King Uzziah died I saw also the Lord, sitting upon a throne high

00:21:38.700 --> 00:21:44.920
and lifted up, and his train filled the temple. Above it stood the seraphims,

00:21:45.060 --> 00:21:52.140
each one had six wings, with twain he covered his face, and with twain he covered his feet,

00:21:52.600 --> 00:22:02.420
and with twain he did fly. And one cried unto another, and said, Holy, Holy, Holy is the Lord

00:22:02.420 --> 00:22:10.880
of hosts, the whole earth is full of his glory. And the posts of the door moved at the voice of

00:22:10.880 --> 00:22:20.240
him that cried, and the house was filled with smoke. Then said I, Woe is me, for I am undone,

00:22:20.640 --> 00:22:26.800
because I am a man of unclean lips, and I dwell in the midst of a people of unclean lips,

00:22:26.800 --> 00:22:34.360
for mine eyes have seen the King, the Lord of hosts. Then flew one of the seraphims unto me,

00:22:34.500 --> 00:22:39.500
having a live coal in his hand, which he had taken with the tongs from off the altar.

00:22:39.820 --> 00:22:47.640
And he laid it upon my mouth, and said, Lo, this hath touched thy lips, and thine iniquity is taken

00:22:47.640 --> 00:22:56.900
away, and thy sin purged. Also I heard the voice of the Lord saying, Whom shall I send,

00:22:57.400 --> 00:23:07.200
and who will go for us? Then said I, Here am I, send me. And he said, Go, and tell this people,

00:23:07.840 --> 00:23:16.770
hear ye indeed, but understand not, and see ye indeed, but perceive not. Make the heart of

00:23:16.770 --> 00:23:25.130
people fat, and make their ears heavy, and shut their eyes, lest they see with their eyes,

00:23:25.650 --> 00:23:32.270
and hear with their ears, and understand with their heart, and convert, and be healed.

00:23:33.070 --> 00:23:40.290
Then said I, Lord, how long? And he answered, Until the cities be wasted without inhabitant,

00:23:41.070 --> 00:23:48.730
and the houses without man, and the land be utterly desolate, and the Lord have removed

00:23:48.730 --> 00:23:57.090
men far away, and there be a great forsaking in the midst of the land. But yet in it shall be a

00:23:57.090 --> 00:24:04.750
tenth, and it shall return, and shall be eaten, as a teal tree, and as an oak, whose substance

00:24:04.750 --> 00:24:11.070
is in them. When they cast their leaves, so the holy seed shall be the substance thereof.

