02:08:13.100 --> 02:08:15.060
THE BOOK OF ISAIAH

02:08:15.060 --> 02:08:17.160
KING JAMES VERSION

02:08:17.160 --> 02:08:19.680
CHAPTER 37

02:08:20.660 --> 02:08:22.820
And it came to pass,

02:08:23.200 --> 02:08:26.100
when King Hezekiah heard it,

02:08:26.400 --> 02:08:28.020
that he rent his clothes,

02:08:28.360 --> 02:08:31.100
and covered himself with sackcloth,

02:08:31.120 --> 02:08:34.820
and went into the house of the Lord.

02:08:35.120 --> 02:08:36.840
And he sent Ilekin,

02:08:37.600 --> 02:08:40.820
who was over the household of Shebna,

02:08:41.180 --> 02:08:42.340
the scribe,

02:08:42.540 --> 02:08:44.160
and the elders of the priests

02:08:44.160 --> 02:08:45.960
covered with sackcloth

02:08:45.960 --> 02:08:47.780
unto Isaiah the prophet,

02:08:47.900 --> 02:08:49.700
the son of Amoz.

02:08:49.940 --> 02:08:51.700
And they said unto him,

02:08:52.140 --> 02:08:54.540
Thus saith Hezekiah,

02:08:54.860 --> 02:08:57.300
This day is a day of trouble,

02:08:57.540 --> 02:08:58.940
and of rebuke,

02:08:59.040 --> 02:09:00.520
and of blasphemy.

02:09:00.980 --> 02:09:03.200
For the children are come to birth,

02:09:03.340 --> 02:09:05.760
and there is not strength

02:09:05.760 --> 02:09:07.140
to bring forth.

02:09:07.900 --> 02:09:10.860
It may be the Lord thy God

02:09:10.860 --> 02:09:14.500
will hear the words of Rebshaka,

02:09:14.500 --> 02:09:16.480
whom the king of Assyria,

02:09:16.520 --> 02:09:18.160
his master, hath sent

02:09:18.160 --> 02:09:21.600
to reproach the living God,

02:09:22.060 --> 02:09:24.140
and will reprove the words

02:09:24.140 --> 02:09:26.740
which the Lord thy God hath heard,

02:09:27.320 --> 02:09:29.160
wherefore lift up thy prayer

02:09:29.160 --> 02:09:31.380
for the remnant that is left.

02:09:31.960 --> 02:09:34.780
So the servants of King Hezekiah

02:09:34.780 --> 02:09:36.620
came to Isaiah,

02:09:36.980 --> 02:09:39.560
and Isaiah said unto them,

02:09:39.840 --> 02:09:42.760
Thus shall ye say unto your master,

02:09:42.760 --> 02:09:44.280
Thus saith the Lord,

02:09:44.660 --> 02:09:46.400
Be not afraid of the words

02:09:46.400 --> 02:09:48.980
of that thou hast heard,

02:09:49.400 --> 02:09:52.060
wherewith the servants of the king of Assyria

02:09:52.060 --> 02:09:54.340
have blasphemed me.

02:09:54.740 --> 02:09:57.920
Behold, I will send a blast upon him,

02:09:58.200 --> 02:09:59.960
and he shall hear a rumor,

02:10:00.340 --> 02:10:03.380
and return to his own land,

02:10:03.600 --> 02:10:06.320
and I will cause him to fall

02:10:06.320 --> 02:10:09.300
by the sword in his own land.

02:10:09.920 --> 02:10:12.940
So Rebshaka returned

02:10:12.940 --> 02:10:14.1000
and found the king of Assyria

02:10:14.1000 --> 02:10:17.380
warring against Libna,

02:10:17.580 --> 02:10:19.760
for he had heard that he was

02:10:19.760 --> 02:10:22.160
departed from Lekish.

02:10:23.100 --> 02:10:26.380
And he heard saying concerning,

02:10:27.180 --> 02:10:29.360
Terhakka, king of Ethiopia,

02:10:29.880 --> 02:10:32.620
he is come forth to make war with thee,

02:10:32.840 --> 02:10:34.420
and when he heard it,

02:10:34.680 --> 02:10:37.520
he sent messages to Hezekiah saying,

02:10:38.020 --> 02:10:41.040
Thus shall ye speak to Hezekiah,

02:10:41.280 --> 02:10:43.120
king of Judah, saying,

02:10:43.480 --> 02:10:47.140
Let not thy God in whom thou trustest

02:10:47.140 --> 02:10:48.260
deceive thee,

02:10:48.680 --> 02:10:50.860
saying Jerusalem shall not be given

02:10:50.860 --> 02:10:53.880
into the hand of the king of Assyria.

02:10:54.340 --> 02:10:56.320
Behold, thou hast heard

02:10:56.320 --> 02:10:58.520
what the kings of Assyria have done

02:10:58.520 --> 02:11:02.340
to all lands by destroying them utterly,

02:11:02.940 --> 02:11:04.800
and shalt thou be delivered?

02:11:04.800 --> 02:11:08.340
Have the gods of the nations delivered them

02:11:08.340 --> 02:11:10.920
which my fathers have destroyed

02:11:10.920 --> 02:11:15.220
in Gozan, and Haran, and Rezef,

02:11:15.420 --> 02:11:17.260
and the children of Eden,

02:11:17.640 --> 02:11:20.160
which were in Tel Azhar?

02:11:20.680 --> 02:11:22.860
Where is the king of Hamath,

02:11:23.120 --> 02:11:24.720
and the king of Arphad,

02:11:25.140 --> 02:11:28.920
and the king of the city of Sephirvaeum,

02:11:29.220 --> 02:11:30.860
Hanna, and Iva?

02:11:31.540 --> 02:11:33.360
And Hezekiah received the letter

02:11:33.360 --> 02:11:35.760
from the hand of the messengers,

02:11:36.160 --> 02:11:39.020
and read it, and Hezekiah went up

02:11:39.020 --> 02:11:41.040
into the house of the Lord,

02:11:41.460 --> 02:11:43.940
and spread it before the Lord,

02:11:44.280 --> 02:11:47.020
and Hezekiah prayed unto the Lord,

02:11:47.260 --> 02:11:50.220
saying, O Lord of hosts,

02:11:50.740 --> 02:11:52.520
God of Israel,

02:11:52.940 --> 02:11:55.420
thou dwellest between the cherubim,

02:11:55.600 --> 02:11:59.100
thou art God even thou alone.

02:11:59.520 --> 02:12:02.020
Of all the kingdoms of the earth,

02:12:02.020 --> 02:12:05.800
thou hast made heaven and earth.

02:12:06.100 --> 02:12:08.700
Incline thine ear, O Lord, and hear.

02:12:09.080 --> 02:12:12.120
Open thine eyes, O Lord, and see,

02:12:12.960 --> 02:12:16.360
and hear all the words of Sennacherib,

02:12:16.580 --> 02:12:20.720
which hath sent to reproach the living God.

02:12:21.520 --> 02:12:23.980
Of a truth, Lord, the kings of Assyria

02:12:23.980 --> 02:12:26.680
have laid waste all the nations

02:12:26.680 --> 02:12:28.300
and their countries,

02:12:28.300 --> 02:12:32.160
and have cast their gods into the fire,

02:12:32.400 --> 02:12:33.780
for they were no gods,

02:12:34.180 --> 02:12:37.940
but the work of men's hands, wood, and stone.

02:12:38.380 --> 02:12:41.120
Therefore, they have destroyed them.

02:12:41.520 --> 02:12:44.740
Now therefore, O Lord, our God,

02:12:45.180 --> 02:12:47.620
save us from His hand,

02:12:47.1000 --> 02:12:51.500
that all the kingdoms of the earth may know

02:12:51.500 --> 02:12:55.480
that thou art the Lord even thou only.

02:12:56.460 --> 02:12:58.820
Then Isaiah, the son of Amoz,

02:12:59.060 --> 02:13:01.800
sent unto Hezekiah, saying,

02:13:02.380 --> 02:13:06.040
Thus saith the Lord God of Israel,

02:13:06.600 --> 02:13:09.940
whereas thou hast prayed to me

02:13:09.940 --> 02:13:13.680
against Sennacherib, king of Assyria,

02:13:14.040 --> 02:13:16.080
this is the word which the Lord

02:13:16.080 --> 02:13:19.100
hath spoken concerning him.

02:13:19.480 --> 02:13:22.140
The virgin, the daughter of Zion,

02:13:22.360 --> 02:13:23.720
hath despised thee,

02:13:23.720 --> 02:13:26.400
and lathed thee to scorn,

02:13:26.780 --> 02:13:28.020
the daughter of Jerusalem

02:13:28.020 --> 02:13:30.840
hath shaken her head at thee.

02:13:31.580 --> 02:13:34.420
Whom hast thou reproached and blasphemed,

02:13:34.680 --> 02:13:38.740
and against whom hast thou exalted thy voice,

02:13:39.100 --> 02:13:41.960
and lifted up thine eyes on high,

02:13:42.340 --> 02:13:45.960
even against the Holy One of Israel?

02:13:46.580 --> 02:13:50.380
By thy servants hast thou reproached the Lord,

02:13:50.380 --> 02:13:54.240
and hast said, by the multitude of my chariots

02:13:54.240 --> 02:13:57.680
am I come up to the height of the mountains,

02:13:58.080 --> 02:14:00.020
to the sides of Lebanon,

02:14:00.280 --> 02:14:03.500
and I will cut down the tall cedars thereof,

02:14:03.820 --> 02:14:06.340
and the choice fir trees thereof,

02:14:06.500 --> 02:14:10.060
and I will enter into the height of His border,

02:14:10.280 --> 02:14:12.620
and the forest of His camel.

02:14:13.260 --> 02:14:16.300
I have digged and drunk water,

02:14:16.540 --> 02:14:19.080
and with the sole of my feet

02:14:19.080 --> 02:14:23.880
have I dried up all the rivers of the besieged places.

02:14:24.420 --> 02:14:28.740
Hast thou not heard long ago how I have done it,

02:14:29.360 --> 02:14:33.380
and of ancient times that I have formed it?

02:14:33.740 --> 02:14:36.300
Now have I brought it to pass,

02:14:37.040 --> 02:14:40.260
that thou shouldest be to lay waste

02:14:40.260 --> 02:14:43.920
defensed cities into ruinous heaps.

02:14:44.040 --> 02:14:48.740
Therefore their inhabitants were of small power,

02:14:48.740 --> 02:14:51.100
they were dismayed and confounded,

02:14:51.440 --> 02:14:54.100
they were as the grass of the field,

02:14:54.520 --> 02:14:56.020
and as the green herb,

02:14:56.220 --> 02:14:59.140
as the grass on the housetops,

02:14:59.400 --> 02:15:03.360
and as corn blasted before it be grown up.

02:15:03.1000 --> 02:15:05.980
But I know thy abode,

02:15:06.300 --> 02:15:08.940
and thy going out and thy coming in,

02:15:09.180 --> 02:15:12.060
and thy rage against me,

02:15:12.540 --> 02:15:14.600
because thy rage against me,

02:15:14.600 --> 02:15:18.1000
and thy tumult is come up into mine ears,

02:15:19.120 --> 02:15:22.440
therefore will I put my hook in thy nose,

02:15:22.840 --> 02:15:25.180
and my bridle in thy lips,

02:15:25.540 --> 02:15:30.440
and I will turn thee back by the way by which thou camest,

02:15:30.680 --> 02:15:33.620
and this shall be a sign unto thee.

02:15:33.960 --> 02:15:38.280
Ye shall eat this year which as groweth of itself,

02:15:38.720 --> 02:15:42.400
and the second year that which springeth of the same,

02:15:42.400 --> 02:15:46.300
and in the third year sow ye and reap,

02:15:46.920 --> 02:15:50.080
and plant vineyards, and eat the fruit thereof.

02:15:50.520 --> 02:15:53.940
And the remnant that is escaped of the house of Judah,

02:15:54.400 --> 02:15:57.960
shall take root downward and bear fruit upward.

02:15:59.280 --> 02:16:03.100
For out of Jerusalem shall go forth a remnant,

02:16:03.480 --> 02:16:06.600
and they that escape out of Mount Zion,

02:16:06.940 --> 02:16:10.260
the zeal of the Lord of hosts shall do this.

02:16:10.260 --> 02:16:12.1000
Therefore, thus sayeth the Lord

02:16:12.1000 --> 02:16:15.640
concerning the king of Assyria,

02:16:16.020 --> 02:16:18.560
he shall not come into this city,

02:16:18.860 --> 02:16:20.920
nor shoot an arrow there,

02:16:21.280 --> 02:16:23.360
nor come before it with shields,

02:16:23.740 --> 02:16:26.100
nor cast a bank against it.

02:16:26.760 --> 02:16:30.560
By the way that he came, by the same shall he return,

02:16:30.940 --> 02:16:35.760
and shall not come into this city, sayeth the Lord.

02:16:36.000 --> 02:16:37.940
For I will defend this city,

02:16:37.940 --> 02:16:40.600
to save it for mine own sake,

02:16:41.000 --> 02:16:43.880
and for my servant David's sake.

02:16:44.660 --> 02:16:47.540
Then the angel of the Lord went forth

02:16:47.540 --> 02:16:50.320
and smote in the camp of the Assyrians

02:16:50.320 --> 02:16:54.280
in hundred and four score and five thousand,

02:16:54.580 --> 02:16:58.160
and when they arose early in the morning,

02:16:58.380 --> 02:17:01.680
behold, they were all dead corpses.

02:17:03.320 --> 02:17:06.760
So Sennacherib, king of Assyria departed

02:17:06.760 --> 02:17:11.820
and went and returned and dwelt at Nineveh,

02:17:11.820 --> 02:17:15.220
and he came to pass as he was worshiping

02:17:15.220 --> 02:17:18.100
in the house of Nishrach, his god,

02:17:18.640 --> 02:17:23.120
that Adramalek and Sherazer,

02:17:23.660 --> 02:17:27.880
his sons, smote him with the sword,

02:17:28.260 --> 02:17:31.640
and they escaped into the land of Armenia,

02:17:31.640 --> 02:17:38.140
and Esharahadon, his son, reigned in his stead.

02:17:38.840 --> 02:17:40.640
Chapter 38.

02:17:41.800 --> 02:17:45.240
In those days was Hezekiah sick unto death,

02:17:45.900 --> 02:17:49.360
and Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz,

02:17:49.740 --> 02:17:52.880
came unto him and said unto him,

02:17:52.980 --> 02:17:57.260
Thus saith the Lord, set thine house in order,

02:17:57.520 --> 02:18:00.160
for thou shalt die and not live.

02:18:00.820 --> 02:18:04.720
Then Hezekiah turned his face toward the wall

02:18:04.720 --> 02:18:09.520
and prayed unto the Lord and said,

02:18:10.120 --> 02:18:13.020
Remember now, O Lord, I beseech thee,

02:18:13.240 --> 02:18:16.620
how I have walked before thee in truth

02:18:16.620 --> 02:18:18.820
and with a perfect heart,

02:18:19.120 --> 02:18:22.120
and have done that which is good in thy sight.

02:18:22.580 --> 02:18:26.340
And Hezekiah wept, soared.

02:18:27.340 --> 02:18:31.080
Then came the word of the Lord to Isaiah saying,

02:18:31.720 --> 02:18:34.200
Go and say to Hezekiah,

02:18:34.500 --> 02:18:38.380
Thus saith the Lord, the God of David, thy father,

02:18:38.740 --> 02:18:43.120
I have heard thy prayer, I have seen thy tears.

02:18:43.860 --> 02:18:50.560
Behold, I will add unto thy days 15 years,

02:18:50.900 --> 02:18:53.600
and I will deliver thee and this city

02:18:53.600 --> 02:18:56.320
out of the hand of the king of Assyria,

02:18:56.620 --> 02:18:59.020
and I will defend this city.

02:18:59.580 --> 02:19:03.460
And this shall be a sign unto thee from the Lord

02:19:03.460 --> 02:19:07.140
that the Lord will do this thing that he hath spoken.

02:19:07.560 --> 02:19:12.160
Behold, I will bring again the shadow of the degrees

02:19:12.160 --> 02:19:17.520
which is gone down in the sundial of Ahaz,

02:19:17.720 --> 02:19:19.260
10 degrees backward.

02:19:19.260 --> 02:19:23.620
So the sun returned, 10 degrees,

02:19:24.040 --> 02:19:27.160
by which degrees it was gone down.

02:19:28.040 --> 02:19:31.420
The writing of Hezekiah, king of Judah,

02:19:32.000 --> 02:19:37.420
when he had been sick and was recovered of his sickness,

02:19:38.040 --> 02:19:41.340
I said in the cutting off of my days,

02:19:41.760 --> 02:19:44.360
I shall go to the gates of the grave.

02:19:44.840 --> 02:19:49.160
I am deprived of the residue of my years.

02:19:49.840 --> 02:19:52.820
I said, I shall not see the Lord,

02:19:52.980 --> 02:19:55.420
even the Lord in the land of the living.

02:19:56.020 --> 02:20:01.660
I shall behold man no more with the inhabitants of the world.

02:20:02.280 --> 02:20:05.580
Mine age is departed and is removed from me

02:20:05.580 --> 02:20:06.980
as a shepherd's tent.

02:20:07.460 --> 02:20:11.120
I have cut off like a weaver my life.

02:20:11.620 --> 02:20:16.880
He will cut me off with pining sickness from day.

02:20:17.240 --> 02:20:21.360
Even tonight wilt thou make an end of me.

02:20:21.820 --> 02:20:25.240
I reckoned till morning that as a lion,

02:20:25.480 --> 02:20:28.140
so will he break all my bones.

02:20:28.740 --> 02:20:33.180
From day even tonight wilt thou make an end of me.

02:20:33.400 --> 02:20:37.640
Like a crane or a swallow, so did I chatter.

02:20:37.700 --> 02:20:40.040
I did mourn as a dove.

02:20:40.040 --> 02:20:43.700
Mine eyes failed with looking upward.

02:20:43.940 --> 02:20:46.260
Oh Lord, I am oppressed.

02:20:46.820 --> 02:20:50.340
Undertake for me, what shall I say?

02:20:51.040 --> 02:20:56.400
He hath both spoken unto me and himself hath done it.

02:20:56.920 --> 02:21:02.380
I shall go softly all my years in the bitterness of my soul.

02:21:02.940 --> 02:21:06.760
Oh Lord, by these things men live.

02:21:06.760 --> 02:21:10.460
And in all these things is the life of my spirit.

02:21:10.900 --> 02:21:15.360
So wilt thou recover me and make me to live.

02:21:15.900 --> 02:21:19.700
Behold for peace, I had great bitterness,

02:21:20.140 --> 02:21:24.680
but thou hast in love to my soul delivered it

02:21:24.680 --> 02:21:26.780
from the pit of corruption.

02:21:27.240 --> 02:21:31.740
For thou hast cast all my sins behind thy back.

02:21:32.440 --> 02:21:34.800
For the grave cannot praise thee.

02:21:34.800 --> 02:21:37.500
Death cannot celebrate thee.

02:21:38.120 --> 02:21:42.940
They that go down into the pit cannot hope for thy truth.

02:21:43.640 --> 02:21:46.660
The living, the living he shall praise thee

02:21:46.660 --> 02:21:48.700
as I do this day.

02:21:49.020 --> 02:21:53.060
The father to the children shall make known thy truth.

02:21:53.540 --> 02:21:55.820
The Lord was ready to save me.

02:21:56.100 --> 02:22:01.100
Therefore we will sing my songs to the stringed instruments

02:22:01.100 --> 02:22:06.420
all the days of our life in the house of the Lord.

02:22:07.040 --> 02:22:11.780
For Isaiah had said, let them take a lump of figs

02:22:11.780 --> 02:22:16.880
and lay it for a plaster upon the boil and he shall recover.

02:22:18.160 --> 02:22:22.620
Hezekiah also had said, what is the sign

02:22:22.620 --> 02:22:27.400
that I shall go up to the house of the Lord?

02:22:27.400 --> 02:22:29.880
Chapter 39.

02:22:30.520 --> 02:22:33.660
At that time, Merodach Baladon,

02:22:33.840 --> 02:22:37.440
the son of Baladon, king of Babylon,

02:22:38.000 --> 02:22:42.080
sent letters and a present to Hezekiah.

02:22:42.420 --> 02:22:47.240
For he had heard that he had been sick and was recovered.

02:22:47.960 --> 02:22:51.140
And Hezekiah was glad of them and showed them

02:22:51.140 --> 02:22:53.960
the house of his precious things,

02:22:53.960 --> 02:22:57.040
the silver and the gold and the spices

02:22:57.040 --> 02:23:01.860
and the precious ointment and all the house of his armor.

02:23:02.240 --> 02:23:05.440
And all that was found in his treasures.

02:23:05.700 --> 02:23:08.260
There was nothing in his house,

02:23:08.280 --> 02:23:13.420
nor in all his dominion that Hezekiah showed them not.

02:23:14.100 --> 02:23:18.660
Then came Isaiah the prophet unto king Hezekiah

02:23:18.660 --> 02:23:23.340
and said unto him, what said these men?

02:23:23.340 --> 02:23:26.440
And from whence came they unto thee?

02:23:27.120 --> 02:23:30.920
And Hezekiah said, they are come from a far country

02:23:30.920 --> 02:23:34.040
unto me, even from Babylon.

02:23:35.140 --> 02:23:39.620
Then said he, what have they seen in thine house?

02:23:40.200 --> 02:23:44.280
And Hezekiah answered, all that is in mine house

02:23:44.280 --> 02:23:48.000
have they seen, there is nothing among my treasures

02:23:48.000 --> 02:23:50.180
that I have not showed them.

02:23:50.920 --> 02:23:54.080
Then said Isaiah to Hezekiah,

02:23:54.640 --> 02:23:57.560
hear the word of the Lord of hosts.

02:23:57.780 --> 02:24:02.900
Behold the days come that all that is in thine house

02:24:02.900 --> 02:24:06.960
and that which thy fathers have laid up in store

02:24:06.960 --> 02:24:11.220
until this day shall be carried to Babylon.

02:24:11.900 --> 02:24:15.640
Nothing shall be left, saith the Lord.

02:24:16.040 --> 02:24:19.140
And of thy sons that shall issue from thee,

02:24:19.140 --> 02:24:24.260
which thou shalt beget, shall they take away

02:24:24.260 --> 02:24:27.580
and they shall be eunuchs in the palace

02:24:27.580 --> 02:24:29.520
of the king of Babylon.

02:24:30.580 --> 02:24:33.780
Then said Hezekiah to Isaiah,

02:24:34.420 --> 02:24:38.440
good is the word of the Lord which thou hast spoken.

02:24:39.040 --> 02:24:42.960
He said moreover, for there shall be peace

02:24:42.960 --> 02:24:45.860
and truth in my days.

02:25:13.360 --> 02:25:19.560
The Book of Isaiah, King James Version, Chapter 40

02:25:20.620 --> 02:25:42.600
Comfort ye, my people, saith your God. Speak ye comfortable to Jerusalem, and cry unto her, that her warfare is accomplished, that her iniquity is pardoned, for she hath received of the Lord's hand double for all her sins.

02:25:42.600 --> 02:25:54.940
The voice of him that crieth in the wilderness, prepare ye the way of the Lord, make straight in the desert a highway for our God.

02:25:54.940 --> 02:26:05.820
Every valley shall be exalted, and every mountain and hill shall be made low, and the crooked shall be made straight and the rough places plain.

02:26:06.320 --> 02:26:15.860
And the glory of the Lord shall be revealed, and all flesh shall see it together. For the mouth of the Lord hath spoken it.

02:26:15.860 --> 02:26:29.140
The voice said, Cry, and he said, What shall I cry? All flesh is grass, and all the goodliness thereof is as the flower of the field.

02:26:29.140 --> 02:26:47.380
The grass withereth, the flower fadeth, because the spirit of the Lord bloweth upon it. Surely the people is grass. The grass withereth, the flower fadeth, but the word of our God shall stand forever.

02:26:47.380 --> 02:27:01.460
O Zion, that bringeth good tidings, get thee up into the high mountain, O Jerusalem, that bringeth good tidings, lift up thy voice with strength.

02:27:01.860 --> 02:27:08.840
Lift it up, be not afraid, say unto the cities of Judah, Behold your God.

02:27:09.620 --> 02:27:23.360
Behold, the Lord God will come with strong hand, and his arm shall rule for him. Behold, his reward is with him, and his work before him.

02:27:23.900 --> 02:27:35.920
He shall feed his flock like a shepherd. He shall gather the lambs with his arm, and carry them in his bosom, and shall gently lead those that are with young.

02:27:35.920 --> 02:27:52.580
Who hath measured the waters in the hollow of his hand, and meted out heaven with the span, and comprehended the dust of the earth in a measure, and weighed the mountains in scales, and the hills in a balance?

02:27:52.580 --> 02:28:14.580
Who hath directed the spirit of the Lord, or, being his counselor, hath taught him? With whom took he counsel, and who instructed him, and taught him in the path of judgment, and taught him knowledge, and showed to him the way of understanding?

02:28:14.580 --> 02:28:28.440
Behold, the nations are as a drop of a bucket, and are counted as the small dust of the balance. Behold, he taketh up the isles as a very little thing.

02:28:28.440 --> 02:28:45.620
And Lebanon is not sufficient to burn, nor the beast thereof sufficient for a burnt offering. All nations before him are as nothing, and they are counted to him less than nothing and vanity.

02:28:45.620 --> 02:29:03.080
To whom then will ye liken God, or what likeness will ye compare unto him? The workman melteth a graven image, and the goldsmith spreadeth it over with gold and casteth silver chains.

02:29:03.080 --> 02:29:23.340
He that is so impoverished that he hath no oblation chooseth a tree that will not rot, he seeketh unto him a cunning workman to prepare a graven image that shall not be moved.

02:29:23.340 --> 02:29:35.600
Have ye not known? Have ye not heard? Hath it not been told you from the beginning? Have ye not understood from the foundations of the earth?

02:29:35.600 --> 02:29:52.220
It is he that sitteth upon the circle of the earth, and the inhabitants thereof are as grasshoppers, that stretcheth out the heavens as a curtain, and spreadeth them out as a tent to dwell in.

02:29:52.220 --> 02:30:17.960
That bringeth the princes to nothing, he maketh the judges of the earth as vanity. Yea, they shall not be planted, yea, they shall not be sown, yea, their stock shall not take root in the earth, and he shall also blow upon them, and they shall wither, and the whirlwind shall take them away as stuple.

02:30:17.960 --> 02:30:44.960
To whom then will ye liken me, or shall I be equal, saith the Holy One? Lift up your eyes on high, and behold, who hath created these things, that bringeth out their host by number? He calleth them all by names, by the greatness of his might, for that he is strong in power, no one faileth.

02:30:44.960 --> 02:30:56.040
Why sayeth thou, O Jacob, and speaketh, O Israel, my way is hid from the Lord, and my judgment is passed over from my God?

02:30:56.040 --> 02:31:18.380
Hast thou not known, hast thou not heard, that the everlasting God, the Lord, the Creator of the ends of the earth, fainteth not? Neither is weary, there is no searching of his understanding, he giveth power to the faint, and to them that have no might, he increaseth strength.

02:31:18.380 --> 02:31:38.880
Even the youths shall faint and be weary, and the young men shall utterly fall, but they that wait upon the Lord shall renew their strength, they shall mount up with wings as eagles, they shall run and not be weary, they shall walk and not faint.

02:31:38.880 --> 02:31:54.340
Chapter 41. Keep silence before me, O islands, and let the people renew their strength, let them come near, let them speak, let us come near together to judgment.

02:31:54.340 --> 02:32:11.960
Who raised up the righteous man from the east, called him to his foot, gave the nations before him, and made him rule over kings. He gave them as the dust to his sword, and as driven stubble to his bowl.

02:32:11.960 --> 02:32:31.040
He pursued them and passed safely, even by the way that he had not gone with his feet, who hath wrought and done it, calling the generations from the beginning, I, the Lord, the first, and with the last, I am he.

02:32:31.040 --> 02:32:45.640
The isles saw it and feared. The ends of the earth were afraid, drew near and came. They helped every one his neighbor, and every one said to his brother, Be of good courage.

02:32:45.640 --> 02:33:05.080
So the carpenter encouraged the goldsmith, and he that smootheth with the hammer, him that smote the anvil, saying, It is ready for the soldering, and he fastened it with nails, that it should not be moved.

02:33:05.080 --> 02:33:29.360
But thou, Israel, art my servant, Jacob, whom I have chosen, the seed of Abraham, my friend, thou whom I have taken from the ends of the earth, and called thee from the chief men thereof, and said unto thee, Thou art my servant, I have chosen thee, and not cast thee away.

02:33:29.360 --> 02:33:45.400
Fear thou not, for I am with thee. Be not dismayed, for I am thy God. I will strengthen thee, yea, I will help thee, yea, I will uphold thee with the right hand of my righteousness.

02:33:45.400 --> 02:33:59.320
Behold, all they that were incensed against thee shall be ashamed and confounded. They shall be as nothing, and they that strive with thee shall perish.

02:33:59.320 --> 02:34:22.260
Thou shalt seek them, and shalt not find them, even them that contended with thee. They that war against thee shall be as nothing, and as a thing of naught. For I, the Lord thy God, will hold thy right hand, saying unto thee, Fear not, I will help thee.

02:34:22.260 --> 02:34:37.980
Fear not, thou worm, Jacob, and ye men of Israel, I will help thee, saith the Lord, and thy Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel. Behold, I will make thee a new sharp threshing instrument.

02:34:37.980 --> 02:34:59.600
Having teeth, thou shalt thresh the mountains and beat them small, and shalt make the hills as shafts. Thou shalt fan them, and the wind shall carry them away, and the whirlwind shall scatter them, and thou shalt rejoice in the Lord, and shalt glory in the Holy One of Israel.

02:35:00.320 --> 02:35:12.200
When the poor and needy seek water, and there is none, and their tongue faileth for thirst, I, the Lord, will hear them. I, the God of Israel, will not forsake them.

02:35:12.200 --> 02:35:24.260
I will open rivers in high places, and fountains in the midst of the valleys. I will make the wilderness a pool of water, and the dry land springs of water.

02:35:24.260 --> 02:35:50.680
I will plant in the wilderness the cedar, the shittar tree, and the myrtle, and the oil tree. I will set in the desert the fir tree and the pine, and the box tree together, that they may see and know and consider and understand together that the hand of the Lord hath done this, and the Holy One of Israel hath created it.

02:35:50.680 --> 02:36:15.780
Produce your cause, saith the Lord. Bring forth your strong reasons, saith the King of Jacob. Let them, bring them forth, and show us what shall happen. Let them show the former things, what they be, that we may consider them, and know the latter end of them, or declare us things for to come.

02:36:15.780 --> 02:36:29.340
Show the things that are to come hereafter, that we may know, that ye are gods, yea, do good or do evil, that we may be dismayed and behold it together.

02:36:30.100 --> 02:36:47.400
Behold, ye are of nothing, and your work of not an abomination is he that chooseth you. I have raised up one from the north, and he shall come from the rising of the sun, shall he call upon my name.

02:36:47.400 --> 02:37:13.260
He shall come upon princes as upon mortar, and as the potter treadeth clay, who hath declared from the beginning that we may know, and before time that we may say he is righteous, yea, there is none that showeth, yea, there is none that declareth, yea, there is none that heareth your words.

02:37:13.260 --> 02:37:35.460
The first shall say to Zion, Behold, behold them, and I will give to Jerusalem one that bringeth good tidings, for I beheld, and there was no man, even among them, and there was no counselor, that when I asked of them could answer a word.

02:37:35.460 --> 02:37:45.780
Behold, they are all vanity, their works are nothing, their molten images are wind and confusion.

02:37:45.780 --> 02:38:02.580
Chapter 42. Behold my servant whom I uphold, mine elect, in whom my soul delighteth. I have put my spirit upon him, he shall bring forth judgment to the Gentiles.

02:38:03.600 --> 02:38:17.760
He shall not cry, nor lift up, nor cause his voice to be heard in the street, a bruised reed shall he not break, and the smoking flax shall he not quench.

02:38:17.760 --> 02:38:30.980
He shall bring forth judgment unto truth, he shall not fail, nor be discouraged, till he have set judgment in the earth, and the isles shall wait for his law.

02:38:30.980 --> 02:38:50.980
Thus saith God, the Lord, he that created the heavens and stretched them out, he that spread forth the earth, and that which cometh out of it, he that giveth breath unto the people, upon it, and spirit to them that walk therein.

02:38:50.980 --> 02:39:16.240
I, the Lord, have called thee in righteousness, and will hold thine hand, and will keep thee, and give thee, for a covenant of the people, for a light of the Gentiles, to open the blind eyes, to bring out the prisoners from the prison, and them that sit in darkness out of the prison house.

02:39:16.240 --> 02:39:27.620
I am the Lord, that is my name, and my glory will I not give to another, neither my praise to graven images.

02:39:28.200 --> 02:39:35.900
Behold, the former things are come to pass, and new things do I declare before they spring forth, I tell you of them.

02:39:36.860 --> 02:39:50.120
Sing unto the Lord a new song, and his praise from the end of the earth, ye that go down to the sea, and all that is therein, the isles and the inhabitants thereof.

02:39:50.120 --> 02:40:09.500
Let the wilderness and the cities thereof lift up their voice, the villages that Kedar doth inhabit, let the inhabitants of the rock sing, let them shout from the top of the mountains, let them give glory unto the Lord and declare his praise in the islands.

02:40:09.500 --> 02:40:23.140
The Lord shall go forth as a mighty man, he shall stir up jealousy like a man of war, he shall cry, yea, roar, he shall prevail against his enemies.

02:40:23.140 --> 02:40:37.540
I have long time holding my peace, I have been still, and refrained myself, now will I cry, like a travailing woman, I will destroy and devour at once.

02:40:37.540 --> 02:40:53.780
I will make waste mountains and hills, and dry up all their herbs, and I will make the rivers islands, and I will dry up the pools, and I will bring the blind by a way that they knew not.

02:40:53.780 --> 02:41:07.780
I will lead them in paths that they have not known, I will make darkness light before them, and crooked things straight, these things will I do unto them, and not forsake them.

02:41:07.780 --> 02:41:19.260
They shall be turned back, they shall be greatly ashamed, that trust engraven images, that say to the molten images, ye are our gods.

02:41:19.260 --> 02:41:45.980
Hear ye death, and look ye blind, that ye may see. Who is blind but my servant, or death as my messenger that I sent? Who is blind as he that is perfect, and blind as the Lord's servant, seeing many things, but thou observest not, opening the ears, but he heareth not.

02:41:45.980 --> 02:42:11.200
The Lord is well pleased for his righteousness' sake, he will magnify the law and make it honorable, but this is a people robbed and spoiled, they are all of them snared in holes, and they are hid in prison houses, they are for a prey, and none delivereth for a spoil, and none saith restore.

02:42:11.200 --> 02:42:27.380
Who among you will give ear to this? Who will hearken and hear for the time to come? Who gave Jacob for a spoil, and Israel to the robbers, did not the Lord, he against whom we have sinned?

02:42:27.380 --> 02:42:53.200
For they would not walk in his ways, neither were they obedient unto his law. Therefore he hath poured upon him the fury of his anger, and the strength of battle, and it hath set him on fire round about, yet he knew not, and it burned him, yet he laid it not to heart.

02:43:49.380 --> 02:44:08.480
When thou passeth through the waters, I will be with thee, and through the rivers they shall not overflow thee. When thou walkest through the fire, thou shalt not be burned, neither shall the flame kindle upon thee.

02:44:08.480 --> 02:44:27.880
For I am the Lord thy God, the Holy One of Israel, thy Savior. I gave Egypt for thy ransom, Ethiopia and Seba for thee. Since thou wast precious in my sight, thou hast been honorable, and I have loved thee.

02:44:27.880 --> 02:44:46.940
Therefore will I give men for thee, and people for thy life. Fear not, for I am with thee. I will bring thy seed from the east and gather thee from the west. I will say to the north, give up, and to the south, keep not back.

02:44:46.940 --> 02:45:04.180
Bring my sons from far, and my daughters from the ends of the earth, even every one that is called by my name. For I have created him for my glory, I have formed him, yea, I have made him.

02:45:04.180 --> 02:45:21.940
Bring forth the blind people that have eyes, and the deaf that have ears. Let all the nations be gathered together, and let the people be assembled. Who among them can declare this, and show us former things?

02:45:21.940 --> 02:45:44.160
Let them bring forth their witnesses that they may be justified, or let them hear and say it is truth. Ye are my witnesses, saith the Lord, and my servant, whom I have chosen, that ye may know and believe me, and understand that I am he.

02:45:44.160 --> 02:46:01.460
Before me there was no God formed, neither shall there be after me. I, even I am the Lord, and beside me there is no savior. I have declared and have saved.

02:46:01.460 --> 02:46:21.960
I have showed when there was no strange God among you, therefore ye are my witnesses, saith the Lord, that I am God. Yea, before the day was I am he, and there is none that can deliver out of my hand.

02:46:21.960 --> 02:46:40.900
I will work, and who shall let it? Thus saith the Lord, your Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel. For your sake I have sent to Babylon, and have brought down all their nobles and the Chaldeans, whose cry is in the ships.

02:46:40.900 --> 02:47:02.220
I am the Lord, your Holy One, the Creator of Israel, your King. Thus saith the Lord, which maketh a way in the sea and a path in the mighty waters, which bringeth forth the chariot and the horse, the army and the power they shall lie down together.

02:47:02.220 --> 02:47:20.180
They shall not rise, they are extinct, they are quenched as toad. Remember ye not the former things, neither consider the things of old. Behold, I will do a new thing, now it shall spring forth.

02:47:20.180 --> 02:47:41.800
Shall ye not know it? I will even make a way in the wilderness and rivers in the desert. The beasts of the field shall honor me, the dragons and the owls, because I give waters in the wilderness and rivers in the desert to give drink to my people, my chosen.

02:47:41.800 --> 02:47:56.740
This people have I formed for myself, they shall show forth my praise. But thou hast not called upon me, O Jacob, but thou hast been weary of me, O Israel.

02:47:56.740 --> 02:48:24.880
Thou hast not brought me the small cattle of thy burnt offerings, neither hast thou honored me with thy sacrifice. I have not caused thee to serve with an offering, nor weary thee with incense. Thou hast brought me no sweet cane with money, neither hast thou filled me with the fat of thy sacrifices, but thou hast made me to serve with thy sins.

02:48:24.880 --> 02:48:46.880
Thou hast wearied me with thine iniquities. I, even I, am he that blotteth out thy transgressions for mine own sake and will not remember thy sins. Put me in remembrance, let us plead together, declare thou that thou mayest be justified.

02:48:46.880 --> 02:49:07.880
Thy first father hath sinned, and thy teachers have transgressed against me. Therefore I have profaned the princes of the sanctuary and have given Jacob to the curse and Israel to reproaches.

02:49:09.240 --> 02:49:31.600
Chapter 44. Yet now hear, O Jacob, my servant, and Israel, whom I have chosen. Thus saith the Lord that made thee and formed thee from the womb, which will help thee. Fear not, O Jacob, my servant, and thou Jezaron, whom I have chosen.

02:49:31.600 --> 02:49:45.800
For I will pour water upon him that is thirsty, and floods upon the dry ground. I will pour my spirit upon thy seed and my blessing upon thine offspring.

02:49:45.800 --> 02:50:10.060
And they shall spring up as among the grass, as willows by the water-courses. One shall say, I am the Lord's, and another shall call himself by the name of Jacob, and another shall subscribe with his hand unto the Lord and surname himself by the name of Israel.

02:50:10.060 --> 02:50:32.140
Thus saith the Lord, the King of Israel, and his Redeemer, the Lord of hosts. I am the first and I am the last, and beside me there is no God, and who as I shall call, and shall declare it, and set it in order for me.

02:50:32.140 --> 02:50:58.640
Since I appointed the ancient people and the things that are coming and shall come, let them show unto them. Fear not, neither be afraid. Have not I told thee from that time and have declared it? Ye are even my witnesses. Is there a God beside me? Yea, there is no God. I know not any.

02:50:58.640 --> 02:51:25.460
They that make a graven image are all of them vanity, and their delectable things shall not profit. And they are their own witnesses. They see not nor know that they may be ashamed. Who hath formed a God or molten a graven image that is profitable for nothing?

02:51:25.460 --> 02:51:41.670
Behold, all his fellows shall be ashamed, and the workmen, they are of men. Let them all be gathered together. Let them stand up, yet they shall fear, and they shall be ashamed together.

02:51:41.670 --> 02:52:00.390
The smith with the tongs both worketh in the coals and fashioneth it with hammers, and worketh it with the strength of his arms. Yea, he is hungry, and his strength faileth. He drinketh no water and is faint.

02:52:00.390 --> 02:52:24.310
The carpenter stretcheth out his rule, he marketh it out with a line, he fitted it with planes, and marketh it out with the compass, and maketh it after the figure of a man, according to the beauty of a man, that it may remain in the house.

02:52:24.310 --> 02:52:39.830
He heweth him down cedars, and taketh the cypress and the oak, which he strengtheneth for himself among the trees of the forest. He planteth in ash, and the rain doth nourish it.

02:52:39.830 --> 02:52:54.430
Then shall it be for a man to burn, for he will take thereof and warm himself. Yea, he kindleeth it and baketh bread. Yea, he maketh a god and worshipeth it.

02:52:54.430 --> 02:53:09.310
He maketh it a graven image, and falleth down thereto. He burneth part thereof in the fire. With part thereof he eateth flesh, he roasteth roast, and is satisfied.

02:53:09.310 --> 02:53:33.450
Yea, he warmeth himself and sayeth, Aha, I am warm. I have seen the fire, and the residue thereof he maketh a god, even his graven image. He falleth down unto it and worshipeth it, and prayeth unto it, and sayeth, Deliver me, for thou art my god.

02:53:33.450 --> 02:53:56.210
They have not known nor understood, for he hath shut their eyes that they cannot see, and their hearts that they cannot understand. And none considereth in his heart, neither is their knowledge nor understanding to say, I have burned part of it in the fire.

02:53:56.210 --> 02:54:12.970
Yea, also I have baked bread upon the coals thereof. I have roasted flesh and eaten it, and shall make the residue thereof an abomination. Shall I fall down to the stock of a tree?

02:54:12.970 --> 02:54:25.470
He feedeth on ashes. A deceived heart hath turned him aside, that he cannot deliver his soul nor say, Is there not a lie in my right hand?

02:54:25.470 --> 02:54:38.570
Remember these, O Jacob and Israel, for thou art my servant, I have formed thee. Thou art my servant, O Israel, thou shalt not be forgotten of me.

02:54:38.570 --> 02:54:49.870
I have blotted out as a thick cloud thy transgressions, and as a cloud thy sins. Return unto me, for I have redeemed thee.

02:54:49.870 --> 02:55:08.470
Sing, O ye heavens, for the Lord hath done it. Shout, ye lower parts of the earth. Break forth into singing, ye mountains, O forest, and every tree therein, for the Lord hath redeemed Jacob, and glorified himself in Israel.

02:55:08.470 --> 02:55:37.650
Thus saith the Lord thy Redeemer, and he that formed thee from the womb, I am the Lord that maketh all things, that stretcheth forth the heavens alone, that spreadeth abroad the earth by myself, that frustrateth the tokens of the liars, and maketh diviners mad, that turneth wise men backward, and maketh their knowledge foolish.

02:55:38.490 --> 02:55:59.390
That confirmeth the word of his servant, and performeth the counsel of his messengers, that saith to Jerusalem, thou shalt be inhabited, and to the cities of Judah, ye shall be built, and I will raise up the decayed places thereof.

02:55:59.390 --> 02:56:21.150
That saith to the deep be dry, and I will dry up thy rivers, that saith to Cyrus, he is my shepherd, and shall perform all my pleasure, even saying to Jerusalem, thou shalt be built, and to the temple thy foundation shall be laid.

02:56:21.150 --> 02:56:45.710
Chapter 45 Thus saith the Lord to his anointed, to Cyrus, whose right hand I have holden to subdue nations before him, and I will loose the loins of kings to open before him the two leaved gates, and the gates shall not be shut.

02:56:45.710 --> 02:57:14.290
I will go before thee, and make the crooked places straight, I will break in pieces the gates of brass, and cut in sunder the bars of iron, and I will give thee the treasures of darkness, and hidden riches of secret places, that thou mayest know that I, the Lord, which call thee by thy name, am the God of Israel.

02:57:14.290 --> 02:57:28.990
For Jacob my servant's sake, and Israel mine elect, I have even called thee by thy name, I have surname thee, though thou hast not known me.

02:57:28.990 --> 02:57:56.190
I am the Lord, and there is none else, there is no God beside me, I girded thee, though thou hast not known me, that they may know from the rising of the sun, and from the west, that there is none beside me, I am the Lord, and there is none else, I formed the light, and created darkness, I make peace, and create evil.

02:57:56.190 --> 02:57:59.990
I, the Lord, do all these things.

02:58:00.490 --> 02:58:14.510
Drop down, ye heavens, from above, and let the skies pour down righteousness, let the earth open, and let them bring forth salvation, and let righteousness spring up together.

02:58:14.510 --> 02:58:33.330
I, the Lord, have created it, woe unto him that striveth with his maker, let the potsherd strive with the potsherd of the earth, shall the clay say to him that fashioneth it, what makest thou, or thy work?

02:58:33.330 --> 02:58:44.450
He hath no hands, woe unto him that saith unto his father, what begettest thou, or to the woman, what hast thou brought forth?

02:58:44.450 --> 02:59:01.150
Thus saith the Lord, the holy one of Israel, and his maker, ask me of things to come concerning my sons, and concerning the work of my hands, command ye me.

02:59:01.150 --> 02:59:13.390
I have made the earth, and created man upon it, I, even my hands, have stretched out the heavens, and all their hosts have I commanded.

02:59:13.390 --> 02:59:29.330
I have raised him up in righteousness, and I will direct all his ways, he shall build my city, and he shall let go my captives, not for price nor reward, saith the Lord of hosts.

02:59:29.330 --> 02:59:43.450
Thus saith the Lord, the labor of Egypt, and merchandise of Ethiopia, and of the Sabians, men of stature, shall come over unto thee, and they shall be thine.

02:59:43.610 --> 02:59:56.950
They shall come after thee in chains, they shall come over, and they shall fall down unto thee, they shall make supplication unto thee, saying, Surely God is in thee.

02:59:56.950 --> 03:00:07.810
And there is none else, there is no God. Verily thou art a God that hidest thyself, O God of Israel, the Savior.

03:00:08.630 --> 03:00:20.170
They shall be ashamed and also confounded, all of them. They shall go to confusion together that are makers of idols.

03:00:20.170 --> 03:00:34.510
But Israel shall be saved in the Lord with an everlasting salvation. Ye shall not be ashamed nor confounded, world without end.

03:00:34.510 --> 03:00:51.370
For thus saith the Lord that created the heavens, God himself that formed the earth and made it, he hath established it, he created it not in vain, he formed it to be inhabited.

03:00:51.370 --> 03:01:04.790
I am the Lord, and there is none else. I have not spoken in secret, in a dark place of the earth. I said not unto the seed of Jacob, Seek ye me in vain.

03:01:04.790 --> 03:01:16.830
I the Lord speak righteousness, I declare things that are right. Assemble yourselves and come, draw near together ye that are escaped of the nations.

03:01:16.830 --> 03:01:34.870
They have no knowledge that set up the wood of their graven image and pray unto a God that cannot save. Tell ye and bring them near, yea, let them take counsel together who hath declared this from ancient time.

03:01:34.870 --> 03:01:53.430
Who hath told it from that time? Have not I the Lord, and there is no God else beside me? A just God and a Savior, there is none beside me. Look unto me and be ye saved, all the ends of the earth.

03:01:53.430 --> 03:02:13.570
For I am God, and there is none else. I have sworn by myself, the word is gone out of my mouth in righteousness and shall not return that unto me. Every knee shall bow, every tongue shall swear.

03:02:13.570 --> 03:02:37.730
Surely shall one say, In the Lord have I righteousness and strength. Even to him shall men come, and all that are incensed against him shall be ashamed. In the Lord shall all the seed of Israel be justified, and shall glory.

03:02:43.570 --> 03:02:50.250
Of the Book of Isaiah

03:03:14.170 --> 03:03:17.530
46 Bell boweth down.

03:03:17.730 --> 03:03:18.730
Nebo stoopeth.

03:03:18.730 --> 03:03:22.090
Their idols were upon the beasts and upon the cattle.

03:03:22.970 --> 03:03:24.890
Your carriages were heavy-loaden.

03:03:25.190 --> 03:03:27.130
They are a burden to the weary beast.

03:03:28.370 --> 03:03:30.430
They stoop, they bow down together.

03:03:30.970 --> 03:03:34.650
They could not deliver the burden, but themselves are gone into captivity.

03:03:35.830 --> 03:03:39.830
Harken unto me, O house of Jacob, and all the remnant of the house of Israel,

03:03:40.210 --> 03:03:44.030
which are borne by me from the belly, which are carried from the womb.

03:03:44.770 --> 03:03:50.250
And even to your old age I am he, and even to whore hairs will I carry you.

03:03:51.010 --> 03:03:52.630
I have made, and I will bear.

03:03:53.290 --> 03:03:56.050
Even I will carry, and will deliver you.

03:03:56.910 --> 03:04:01.610
To whom will ye liken me, and make me equal, and compare me that we may be like?

03:04:02.410 --> 03:04:05.790
They lavish gold out of the bag, and weigh silver in the balance,

03:04:06.110 --> 03:04:09.410
and hire a goldsmith, and he maketh it a god.

03:04:09.910 --> 03:04:12.330
They fall down, yea, they worship.

03:04:12.970 --> 03:04:16.650
They bear him upon the shoulder, they carry him, and set him in his place,

03:04:17.070 --> 03:04:18.110
and he standeth.

03:04:18.450 --> 03:04:20.430
From his place shall he not remove.

03:04:21.290 --> 03:04:27.350
Yea, one shall cry unto him, yet can he not answer, nor save him out of his trouble.

03:04:29.170 --> 03:04:31.530
Remember this, and show yourselves men.

03:04:32.050 --> 03:04:34.990
Bring it again to mind, O ye transgressors.

03:04:35.830 --> 03:04:40.730
Remember the former things of old, for I am God, and there is none else.

03:04:41.290 --> 03:04:44.330
I am God, and there is none like me.

03:04:45.710 --> 03:04:50.330
Declaring the end from the beginning, and from ancient times the things that are not yet done,

03:04:50.830 --> 03:04:54.170
saying my council shall stand, and I will do all my pleasure.

03:04:55.470 --> 03:05:00.730
Calling a ravenous bird from the east, the man that executeth my council from a far country.

03:05:01.550 --> 03:05:04.670
Yea, I have spoken it, I will also bring it to pass.

03:05:05.130 --> 03:05:08.270
I have purposed it, I will also do it.

03:05:09.330 --> 03:05:13.370
Harken unto me, ye stout-hearted, that are far from righteousness.

03:05:14.450 --> 03:05:15.930
I bring near my righteousness.

03:05:16.410 --> 03:05:19.410
It shall not be far off, and my salvation shall not tarry,

03:05:19.570 --> 03:05:22.750
and I will place salvation in Zion for Israel my glory.

03:05:24.310 --> 03:05:25.350
Chapter 47

03:05:25.950 --> 03:05:29.430
Come down and sit on the dust, O virgin daughter of Babylon.

03:05:29.870 --> 03:05:30.770
Sit on the ground.

03:05:31.270 --> 03:05:33.830
There is no throne, O daughter of the Chaldeans,

03:05:34.250 --> 03:05:36.670
for thou shalt no more be called tender and delicate.

03:05:37.510 --> 03:05:39.750
Take the millstones and grind meal.

03:05:40.390 --> 03:05:42.570
Uncover thy locks, make bare the leg.

03:05:42.950 --> 03:05:45.630
Uncover the thigh, pass over the rivers.

03:05:46.350 --> 03:05:49.910
Thy nakedness shall be uncovered, yea, thy shame shall be seen.

03:05:50.330 --> 03:05:53.270
I will take vengeance, and I will not meet thee as a man.

03:05:54.230 --> 03:05:58.850
As for our Redeemer, the Lord of hosts is his name, the Holy One of Israel.

03:06:00.430 --> 03:06:04.170
Sit thou silent, and get thee into darkness, O daughter of the Chaldeans,

03:06:04.170 --> 03:06:07.530
for thou shalt no more be called the Lady of kingdoms.

03:06:08.910 --> 03:06:10.550
I was wroth with my people.

03:06:10.870 --> 03:06:14.150
I have polluted mine inheritance and given them into thine hand.

03:06:14.850 --> 03:06:16.650
Thou didst show them no mercy.

03:06:17.250 --> 03:06:20.410
Upon the Ancient hast thou very heavily laid thy yoke.

03:06:21.890 --> 03:06:24.670
And thou saidst, I shall be a Lady forever,

03:06:25.190 --> 03:06:27.710
so that thou didst not lay these things to thy heart,

03:06:27.990 --> 03:06:30.090
neither didst remember the latter end of it.

03:06:31.270 --> 03:06:34.950
Therefore hear now this, thou that art given to pleasures,

03:06:35.430 --> 03:06:38.350
that dwellest carelessly, that sayest in thine heart,

03:06:38.730 --> 03:06:42.550
I am and none else beside me, I shall not sit as a widow,

03:06:42.930 --> 03:06:44.930
neither shall I know the loss of children.

03:06:45.970 --> 03:06:49.510
But these two things shall come to thee in a moment and one day,

03:06:49.870 --> 03:06:52.010
the loss of children and widowhood.

03:06:52.250 --> 03:06:56.470
They shall come upon thee in their perfection for the multitude of thy sorceries,

03:06:56.690 --> 03:06:58.770
and for the great abundance of thine enchantments.

03:07:00.090 --> 03:07:04.650
For thou hast trusted in thy wickedness, thou hast said, none seeth me.

03:07:05.630 --> 03:07:08.670
Thy wisdom and thy knowledge, it hath perverted thee,

03:07:08.930 --> 03:07:13.550
and thou hast said in thine heart, I am and none else beside me.

03:07:14.510 --> 03:07:16.710
Therefore shall evil come upon thee.

03:07:17.010 --> 03:07:20.610
Thou shalt not know from whence it riseth and mischief shall fall upon thee,

03:07:20.870 --> 03:07:22.590
thou shalt not be able to put it off,

03:07:22.950 --> 03:07:26.950
and desolation shall come upon thee suddenly which thou shalt not know.

03:07:28.530 --> 03:07:33.350
Stand now, with thine enchantments, and with the multitude of thy sorceries,

03:07:33.550 --> 03:07:35.490
wherein thou hast laboured from thy youth,

03:07:35.810 --> 03:07:39.930
if so be thou shalt be able to profit, if so be thou mayest prevail.

03:07:41.410 --> 03:07:43.530
Thou art wearied in the multitude of thy counsels.

03:07:44.670 --> 03:07:48.750
Let now the astrologers, the stargazers, the monthly prognosticators,

03:07:48.990 --> 03:07:52.370
stand up and save thee from these things that shall come upon thee.

03:07:53.470 --> 03:07:56.850
Behold, they shall be as stubble, the fire shall burn them,

03:07:56.850 --> 03:07:59.650
they shall not deliver themselves from the power of the flame,

03:08:00.150 --> 03:08:03.830
there shall not be a cold to warm at, nor fire to sit before it.

03:08:04.850 --> 03:08:07.830
Thus shall they be unto thee with whom thou hast laboured,

03:08:08.150 --> 03:08:09.930
even thy merchants from thy youth,

03:08:10.370 --> 03:08:14.330
they shall wander every one to his quarter, none shall save thee.

03:08:16.290 --> 03:08:17.250
Chapter 48

03:08:17.770 --> 03:08:21.250
Hear ye this, O house of Jacob, which are called by the name of Israel,

03:08:21.530 --> 03:08:23.530
and are come forth out of the waters of Judah,

03:08:23.530 --> 03:08:27.650
which swear by the name of the Lord, and make mention of the God of Israel,

03:08:27.910 --> 03:08:29.810
but not in truth nor in righteousness.

03:08:30.550 --> 03:08:34.990
For they call themselves of the holy city, and stay themselves upon the God of Israel.

03:08:35.270 --> 03:08:37.010
The Lord of hosts is his name.

03:08:38.130 --> 03:08:40.590
I have declared the former things from the beginning,

03:08:41.110 --> 03:08:44.190
and they went forth out of my mouth, and I showed them.

03:08:44.490 --> 03:08:47.270
I did them suddenly, and they came to pass,

03:08:47.610 --> 03:08:51.950
because I knew that thou art obstinate, and thy neck is an iron sinew,

03:08:51.950 --> 03:08:53.390
and thy brow brass.

03:08:54.270 --> 03:08:56.550
I have even from the beginning declared it to thee,

03:08:56.690 --> 03:08:59.050
before it came to pass I showed it to thee,

03:08:59.170 --> 03:09:02.350
lest thou shouldest say, mine idol hath done them,

03:09:02.370 --> 03:09:05.810
and my graven image, and my molten image hath commanded them.

03:09:06.910 --> 03:09:11.390
Thou hast heard, see all this, and will not ye declare it?

03:09:11.690 --> 03:09:14.250
I have showed thee new things from this time,

03:09:14.430 --> 03:09:16.910
even hidden things, and thou didst not know them.

03:09:17.790 --> 03:09:20.550
They are created now, and not from the beginning,

03:09:20.550 --> 03:09:23.450
even before the day when thou hurtest them not,

03:09:23.670 --> 03:09:26.710
lest thou shouldest say, behold, I knew them.

03:09:28.930 --> 03:09:32.510
Yea, thou hurtest not, yea, thy knewest not.

03:09:33.370 --> 03:09:36.130
Yea, from that time thine ear was not opened,

03:09:36.570 --> 03:09:39.790
for I knew that thou wouldest deal very treacherously,

03:09:40.050 --> 03:09:42.470
and was called a transgressor from the womb.

03:09:43.670 --> 03:09:46.190
For my name's sake will I defer mine anger,

03:09:46.390 --> 03:09:50.250
and for my praise will I refrain for thee, that I cut thee not off.

03:09:51.310 --> 03:09:54.110
Behold, I have refined thee, but not with silver.

03:09:54.750 --> 03:09:57.470
I have chosen thee in the furnace of affliction.

03:09:58.370 --> 03:10:01.350
For mine own sake, even for mine own sake, will I do it,

03:10:01.450 --> 03:10:03.010
for how should my name be polluted,

03:10:03.250 --> 03:10:05.490
and I will not give my glory unto another.

03:10:06.450 --> 03:10:10.010
Harken unto me, O Jacob and Israel, my called.

03:10:10.670 --> 03:10:14.890
I am he, I am the first, I also am the last.

03:10:15.910 --> 03:10:18.670
Mine hand also hath laid the foundation of the earth,

03:10:18.670 --> 03:10:20.930
and my right hand hath spanned the heavens.

03:10:21.390 --> 03:10:23.830
When I call unto them, they stand up together.

03:10:24.930 --> 03:10:27.270
All ye, assemble yourselves and hear,

03:10:27.470 --> 03:10:29.470
which among them hath declared these things.

03:10:30.010 --> 03:10:33.590
The Lord hath loved him, he will do his pleasure on Babylon,

03:10:33.930 --> 03:10:35.950
and his arm shall be on the Chaldeans.

03:10:36.970 --> 03:10:40.250
I, even I, have spoken, yea, I have called him.

03:10:40.930 --> 03:10:43.930
I have brought him, and he shall make his way prosperous.

03:10:45.110 --> 03:10:48.070
Come ye near unto me, hear ye this.

03:10:48.070 --> 03:10:50.570
I have not spoken in secret from the beginning.

03:10:51.030 --> 03:10:53.390
From the time that it was, there am I,

03:10:53.610 --> 03:10:57.210
and now the Lord God and his Spirit hath sent me.

03:10:58.290 --> 03:11:01.430
Thus saith the Lord thy Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel.

03:11:01.990 --> 03:11:05.550
I am the Lord thy God, which teacheth thee to profit,

03:11:06.090 --> 03:11:08.930
which leadeth thee by the way that thou shouldest go.

03:11:09.830 --> 03:11:12.070
O that thou hadst hearkened to my commandments,

03:11:12.850 --> 03:11:14.910
then had thy peace been as a river,

03:11:15.310 --> 03:11:17.530
and thy righteousness as the waves of the sea.

03:11:18.070 --> 03:11:20.450
Thy seed also had been as the sand,

03:11:20.610 --> 03:11:23.590
and the offspring of thy bowels like the gravel thereof.

03:11:23.890 --> 03:11:27.430
His name should not have been cut off nor destroyed from before me.

03:11:28.430 --> 03:11:32.030
Go ye forth of Babylon, flee ye from the Chaldeans,

03:11:32.150 --> 03:11:33.930
with a voice of singing declare ye,

03:11:34.150 --> 03:11:37.270
tell this, utter it even to the end of the earth.

03:11:37.870 --> 03:11:41.070
Say ye, the Lord hath redeemed his servant Jacob,

03:11:41.370 --> 03:11:44.450
and they thirsted not when he led them through the deserts.

03:11:44.450 --> 03:11:47.090
He caused the waters to flow out of the rock for them.

03:11:47.090 --> 03:11:50.410
He claved the rock also, and the waters gushed out.

03:11:51.090 --> 03:11:54.250
There is no peace, saith the Lord unto the wicked.

03:12:49.270 --> 03:13:01.410
He made my mouth like a sharp sword in the shadow of his hand, hath he hidden me? And made me a polished shaft in his quiver, hath he hidden me?

03:13:01.930 --> 03:13:11.890
And said unto me, Thou art my servant, O Israel, in whom I will be glorified.

03:13:11.890 --> 03:13:26.710
Then I said, I have labored in vain, I have spent my strength for naught, and in vain, yet surely my judgment is with the Lord, and my work with my God.

03:13:26.710 --> 03:13:45.810
And now saith the Lord, that formed me from the womb, to be his servant, to bring Jacob again to him, though Israel be not gathered, yet shall I be glorious in the eyes of the Lord, and my God shall be my strength.

03:13:46.650 --> 03:13:59.910
And he said, It is a light thing, that thou shouldest be my servant, to raise up the tribes of Jacob, and to restore the preserved of Israel.

03:13:59.910 --> 03:14:09.450
I will also give thee for a light to the Gentiles, that thou mayest be my salvation unto the end of the earth.

03:14:09.450 --> 03:14:35.750
Thus saith the Lord, the Redeemer of Israel, and his Holy One, to him whom man despiseth, to him whom the nation abhorreth, to a servant of rulers, kings shall see and arise, princes also shall worship, because of the Lord that is faithful, and the Holy One of Israel, and he shall choose thee.

03:14:35.750 --> 03:14:58.970
Thus saith the Lord, in an acceptable time have I heard thee, and in a day of salvation have I helped thee, and I will preserve thee, and give thee for a covenant of the people, to establish the earth, to cause, to inherit the desolate heritages.

03:14:58.970 --> 03:15:21.730
That thou mayest say to the prisoners, go forth, to them that are in darkness, show yourselves, they shall feed in the waves, and their pastors shall be in all high places, they shall not hunger nor thirst, neither shall the heat nor the sun smite them.

03:15:21.730 --> 03:15:29.790
For he that hath mercy on them shall lead them, even by the springs of water shall he guide them.

03:15:29.790 --> 03:15:46.770
And I will make all my mountains a way, and my highways shall be exalted. Behold, these shall come from far and low, these from the north and from the west, and these from the land of synonym.

03:15:46.770 --> 03:16:00.950
Sing, O heavens, and be joyful, O earth, and break forth into singing, O mountains, for the Lord hath comforted his people, and will have mercy upon his afflicted.

03:16:00.950 --> 03:16:16.470
But Zion said, The Lord hath forsaken me, and my Lord hath forgotten me. Can a woman forget her sucking child, that she should not have compassion on the son of her womb?

03:16:16.470 --> 03:16:39.090
Yea, they may forget, yet will I not forget thee. Behold, I have graven thee upon the palms of my hands, thy walls are continually before me, thy children shall make haste, thy destroyers and they that made thee waste shall go forth of thee.

03:16:39.090 --> 03:17:00.810
Lift up thine eyes, round about, and behold, all these gather themselves together and come to thee. As I live, saith the Lord, thou shalt surely clothe thee with them all, as with an ornament, and bind them on thee as a bride doeth.

03:17:00.810 --> 03:17:16.270
For thy waste and thy desolate places and the land of thy destruction shall even now be too narrow by reason of the inhabitants, and they that swallowed thee up shall be far away.

03:17:16.270 --> 03:17:30.470
The children which thou shalt have, after thou hast lost the other, shall say again in thine ears, The place is too straight for me, give place to me, that I may dwell.

03:17:30.470 --> 03:17:52.590
Then shalt thou say in thine heart, Who have begotten me? These, seeing I have lost my children and am desolate, a captive and removing to and fro, and who have brought up these? Behold, I was left alone, these, where had they been?

03:17:52.590 --> 03:18:15.470
Thus saith the Lord God, Behold, I will lift up mine hand to the Gentiles, and set up my standard to the people, and they shall bring thy sons in their arms, and thy daughters shall be carried upon their shoulders, and kings shall be thy nursing fathers and their queens thy nursing mothers.

03:18:15.470 --> 03:18:31.110
They shall bow down to thee with their face toward the earth, and lick up the dust of thy feet, and thou shalt know that I am the Lord. For they shall not be ashamed that wait for me.

03:18:31.110 --> 03:18:46.030
Shall the prey be taken from the mighty or the lawful captive delivered? But thus saith the Lord, Even the captives of the mighty shall be taken away, and the prey of the terrible shall be delivered.

03:18:46.030 --> 03:19:03.230
For I will contend with them that contendeth with thee, and I will save thy children, and I will feed them that oppress thee with their own flesh, and they shall be drunken with their own blood, as with sweet wine.

03:19:03.230 --> 03:19:14.410
And all flesh shall know that I, the Lord, am thy Savior, and thy Redeemer, the Mighty One of Jacob.

03:19:14.410 --> 03:19:30.650
Chapter 50. Thus saith the Lord, Where is the bill of your mother's divorcement, whom I have put away? Or which of my creditors is it to whom I have sold you?

03:19:30.650 --> 03:19:47.650
Behold, for your iniquities have ye sold yourselves, and for your transgressions is your mother put away. Wherefore, when I came, was there no man? When I called, was there none to answer?

03:19:47.650 --> 03:20:08.110
Is my hand shortened at all, that it cannot redeem? Or have I no power to deliver? Behold, at my rebuke I dry up the sea, I make the rivers in wilderness, their fish stinketh, because there is no water and dieth for thirst.

03:20:08.110 --> 03:20:25.490
I clothe the heavens with blackness, and I make sackcloth their covering. The Lord God hath given me the tongue of the learned, that I should know how to speak a word in season to him that is weary.

03:20:25.490 --> 03:20:40.190
He waketh morning by morning, he waketh mine ear to hear as the learned. The Lord God hath opened mine ear, and I was not rebellious, neither turned away back.

03:20:40.190 --> 03:21:06.070
I gave my back to the smiters and my cheeks to them that plucked off the hair. I hid not my face from shame and spitting. For the Lord God will help me, therefore shall I not be confounded. Therefore have I set my face like a flint, and I know that I shall not be ashamed.

03:21:06.070 --> 03:21:32.310
He is near that justifieth me. Who will contend with me? Let us stand together. Who is my adversary? Let him come near to me. Behold, the Lord God will help me. Who is he that shall condemn me? Lo, they all shall wax old as a garment, the moth shall eat them up.

03:21:32.310 --> 03:21:47.130
Who is among you that feareth the Lord, that obeyeth the voice of his servant, that walketh in darkness and hath no light? Let him trust in the name of the Lord and stay upon his God.

03:21:47.130 --> 03:22:05.870
Behold, all ye that kindle a fire, that compass yourselves about with sparks, walk in the light of your fire, and in the sparks that ye have kindled. This shall ye have of mine hand. Ye shall lie down in sorrow.

03:22:09.790 --> 03:22:24.190
Harken unto me, ye that follow after righteousness, ye that seek the Lord. Look unto the rock whence ye are hewn, and to the hole of the pit whence ye are digged.

03:22:24.190 --> 03:22:37.470
Look unto Abraham, your father, and unto Sarah that bare you. For I called him alone, and blessed him, and increased him. For the Lord shall comfort Zion.

03:22:37.470 --> 03:22:54.810
He will comfort all her waste places, and he will make her wilderness like Eden, and her desert like the garden of the Lord. Joy and gladness shall be found therein, thanksgiving and the voice of melody.

03:22:54.810 --> 03:23:10.870
Harken unto me, my people, and give ear unto me, O my nation, for a law shall proceed from me, and I will make my judgment to rest for a light of the people.

03:23:10.870 --> 03:23:25.230
My righteousness is near, my salvation is gone forth, and mine arms shall judge the people. The isles shall wait upon me, and on mine arms shall they trust.

03:23:25.230 --> 03:23:43.090
Lift up your eyes to the heavens and look upon the earth beneath, for the heavens shall vanish away like smoke, and the earth shall wax old like a garment, and they that dwell therein shall die in like manner.

03:23:43.090 --> 03:23:51.090
But my salvation shall be forever, and my righteousness shall not be abolished.

03:23:51.890 --> 03:24:05.970
Harken unto me, ye that know righteousness, the people in whose heart is my law. Fear ye not the reproach of men, neither be ye afraid of their revilings.

03:24:05.970 --> 03:24:20.970
For the moth shall eat them up like a garment, and the worm shall eat them like wool. But my righteousness shall be forever, and my salvation from generation to generation.

03:24:21.850 --> 03:24:50.950
Awake, awake, put on strength, O arm of the Lord, awake, as in the ancient days, in the generations of old. Art thou not it that hath cut Rahab and wounded the dragon? Art thou not it which hath dried the sea, the waters of the great deep, that have made the depths of the sea a way for the ransomed to pass over?

03:24:50.950 --> 03:25:09.190
Therefore the redeemed of the Lord shall return, and come with singing unto Zion, and everlasting joy shall be upon their head. They shall obtain gladness and joy, and sorrow and mourning shall flee away.

03:25:09.190 --> 03:25:25.010
I, even I, am he that comforteth you. Who art thou that thou shouldest be afraid of a man that shall die, and of the Son of Man which shall be made as grass?

03:25:25.010 --> 03:25:47.870
And forgettest the Lord thy Maker that has stretched forth the heavens, and laid the foundations of the earth, and has feared continually every day because of the fury of the oppressor, as if he were ready to destroy? And where is the fury of the oppressor?

03:25:47.870 --> 03:25:59.950
The captive exiled hasteneth that he may be loosed, and that he should not die in the pit, nor that his bread shall fail.

03:25:59.950 --> 03:26:25.370
But I am the Lord thy God that divided the sea, whose waves roared. The Lord of hosts is his name. And I have put my words in thy mouth, and I have covered thee in the shadow of mine hand, that I may plant the heavens, and lay the foundations of the earth, and say unto Zion, thou art my people.

03:26:26.050 --> 03:26:40.510
Awake, awake, stand up, O Jerusalem, which hast drunk at the hand of the Lord the cup of his fury. Thou hast drunken the dregs of the cup of trembling, and wrung them out.

03:26:40.510 --> 03:26:54.310
There is none to guide her among all the sons whom she hath brought forth. Neither is there any that taketh her by the hand of all the sons that she hath brought up.

03:26:54.310 --> 03:27:07.890
These two things come unto thee. Who shall be sorry for thee, desolation and destruction, and the famine and the sword? By whom shall I comfort thee?

03:27:07.890 --> 03:27:21.250
Thy sons have fainted. They lie at the head of all the streets as a wild bull in a net. They are full of the fury of the Lord, the rebuke of thy God.

03:27:21.250 --> 03:27:43.050
Therefore hear now this, thou afflicted and drunken, but not with wine. Thus saith thy Lord the Lord, and thy God, that pleadeth the cause of his people, Behold, I have taken out of thine hand the cup of trembling.

03:27:43.050 --> 03:28:08.310
Even the dregs of the cup of my fury, thou shalt no more drink it again. But I will put it into the hand of them that afflict thee, which have said to thy soul, bow down, that we may go over, and thou hast laid thy body as the ground and as the street to them that went over.

03:28:13.110 --> 03:28:20.670
This was the story of Isaiah 51

03:28:38.130 --> 03:28:48.630
52. Awake, awake, put on thy strength, O Zion, put on thy beautiful garments, O Jerusalem,

03:28:50.110 --> 03:28:56.830
for henceforth there shall no more come into thee the uncircumcised and the unclean. Shake

03:28:56.830 --> 03:29:03.150
thyself from the dust, arise and sit down, O Jerusalem, loose thyself from the bands of

03:29:03.150 --> 03:29:10.270
thy knack, O captive daughter of Zion. For thus saith the Lord, ye have sold yourselves for not,

03:29:10.530 --> 03:29:17.170
and ye shall be redeemed without money. For thus saith the Lord God, My people went down a four

03:29:17.170 --> 03:29:24.470
time into Egypt to sojourn there, and the Assyrian oppressed them without cause. Now therefore what

03:29:24.470 --> 03:29:30.950
have I here, saith the Lord, that My people is taken away for not? They that rule over them

03:29:30.950 --> 03:29:38.130
make them to howl, saith the Lord, and My name continually every day is blasphemed. Therefore

03:29:38.130 --> 03:29:44.230
My people shall know My name, therefore they shall know in that day that I am He that doth

03:29:44.230 --> 03:29:51.750
speak, behold it is I. How beautiful upon the mountains are the feet of Him that bringeth good

03:29:51.750 --> 03:29:58.070
tidings, that publisheth peace, that bringeth good tidings of good, that publisheth salvation,

03:29:58.730 --> 03:30:05.770
that saith unto Zion, Thy God reigneth. Thy watchmen shall lift up the voice, with the voice

03:30:05.770 --> 03:30:12.350
together shall they sing, for they shall see eye to eye when the Lord shall bring again Zion.

03:30:13.010 --> 03:30:19.870
Break forth into joy, sing together ye waste places of Jerusalem, for the Lord hath comforted

03:30:19.870 --> 03:30:27.170
His people, He hath redeemed Jerusalem. The Lord hath made bare His holy arm in the eyes of all

03:30:27.170 --> 03:30:34.710
the nations, and all the ends of the earth shall see the salvation of our God. Depart ye, depart ye,

03:30:34.830 --> 03:30:41.750
go ye out from thence, touch no unclean thing, go ye out of the midst of her, be ye clean,

03:30:41.750 --> 03:30:48.790
that bear the vessels of the Lord. For ye shall not go out with haste, nor go by flight, for the

03:30:48.790 --> 03:30:56.050
Lord will go before you, and the God of Israel will be your reward. Behold, My servant shall deal

03:30:56.050 --> 03:31:03.350
prudently, he shall be exalted and extolled and be very high. As many were astonied at thee,

03:31:03.690 --> 03:31:10.570
His visage was so marred more than any man, and His form more than the sons of men. So shall

03:31:10.570 --> 03:31:16.850
He sprinkle many nations, the kings shall shut their mouths at Him, for that which had not been

03:31:16.850 --> 03:31:22.270
told them shall they see, and that which they had not heard shall they consider.

03:31:23.810 --> 03:31:30.510
Chapter 53 Who hath believed our report, and to whom is the arm of the Lord revealed? For

03:31:30.510 --> 03:31:36.930
He shall grow up before Him as a tender plant, and as a root out of a dry ground. He hath no

03:31:36.930 --> 03:31:43.470
form nor comeliness, and when we shall see Him there is no beauty that we should desire Him.

03:31:43.950 --> 03:31:50.890
He is despised and rejected of men, a man of sorrows and acquainted with grief, and we hid,

03:31:50.950 --> 03:31:59.210
as it were, our faces from Him. He was despised and we esteemed Him not. Surely He hath borne our

03:31:59.210 --> 03:32:05.770
griefs and carried our sorrows, yet we did esteem Him stricken, smitten of God and afflicted.

03:32:05.770 --> 03:32:13.210
But He was wounded for our transgressions, He was bruised for our iniquities, the chastisement

03:32:13.210 --> 03:32:20.950
of our peace was upon Him, and with His stripes we are healed. All we, like sheep, have gone astray,

03:32:21.190 --> 03:32:27.550
we have turned every one to His own way, and the Lord hath laid on Him the iniquity of us all.

03:32:27.910 --> 03:32:34.710
He was oppressed, and He was afflicted, yet He opened not His mouth. He is brought as a lamb

03:32:34.710 --> 03:32:40.950
to the slaughter, and as a sheep before her shearers is dumb, so He openeth not His mouth.

03:32:41.530 --> 03:32:48.490
He was taken from prison and from judgment, and who shall declare His generation? For He was cut

03:32:48.490 --> 03:32:53.910
off out of the land of the living, for the transgression of My people was He stricken.

03:32:54.590 --> 03:33:00.410
And He made His grave with the wicked and with the rich in His death, because He had done no

03:33:00.410 --> 03:33:07.310
violence, neither was any deceit in His mouth. Yet it pleased the Lord to bruise Him, He hath put

03:33:07.310 --> 03:33:13.490
Him to grief. When Thou shalt make His soul an offering for sin, He shall see His seed,

03:33:13.670 --> 03:33:20.050
He shall prolong His days, and the pleasure of the Lord shall prosper in His hand. He shall see

03:33:20.050 --> 03:33:26.250
the travail of His soul, and shall be satisfied. By His knowledge shall My righteous servant

03:33:26.250 --> 03:33:33.110
justify many, for He shall bear their iniquities. Therefore will I divide Him a portion with the

03:33:33.110 --> 03:33:38.930
great, and He shall divide the spoil with the strong, because He hath poured out His soul unto

03:33:38.930 --> 03:33:45.450
death, and He was numbered with the transgressors, and He bare the sin of many and made intercession

03:33:45.450 --> 03:33:54.850
for the transgressors. Chapter 54 Sing, O barren, thou that didst not bear, break forth into singing

03:33:54.850 --> 03:34:01.430
and cry aloud, thou that didst not travail with child. For more are the children of the desolate

03:34:01.430 --> 03:34:07.890
than the children of the married wife, saith the Lord. Enlarge the place of thy tent, and let them

03:34:07.890 --> 03:34:14.470
stretch forth the curtains of thine habitations. Spare not, lengthen thy cords, and strengthen thy

03:34:14.470 --> 03:34:20.970
stakes. For thou shalt break forth on the right hand and on the left, and thy seed shall inherit

03:34:20.970 --> 03:34:28.570
the Gentiles, and make the desolate cities to be inhabited. Fear not, for thou shalt not be ashamed,

03:34:29.010 --> 03:34:35.130
neither be thou confounded, for thou shalt not be put to shame, for thou shalt forget the shame

03:34:35.130 --> 03:34:42.330
of thy youth, and shalt not remember the reproach of thy widowhood any more. For thy Maker is thine

03:34:42.330 --> 03:34:49.430
husband, the Lord of hosts is His name, and thy Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel, the God of the

03:34:49.430 --> 03:34:56.410
earth shall He be called. For the Lord hath called thee as a woman forsaken and grieved in spirit,

03:34:56.710 --> 03:35:04.610
and a wife of youth, when thou wast refused, saith thy God. For a small moment have I forsaken thee,

03:35:04.870 --> 03:35:11.610
but with great mercies will I gather thee. In a little wrath I hid my face from thee for a moment,

03:35:12.010 --> 03:35:17.610
but with everlasting kindness will I have mercy on thee, saith the Lord thy Redeemer.

03:35:18.330 --> 03:35:24.690
For this is as the waters of Noah unto me, for as I have sworn that the waters of Noah

03:35:24.690 --> 03:35:30.270
should no more go over the earth, so have I sworn that I would not be wroth with thee,

03:35:30.570 --> 03:35:37.370
nor rebuke thee. For the mountains shall depart and the hills be removed, but my kindness shall

03:35:37.370 --> 03:35:43.450
not depart from thee, neither shall the covenant of my peace be removed, saith the Lord that hath

03:35:43.450 --> 03:35:50.950
mercy on thee. O thou afflicted, tossed with tempest, and not comforted, behold, I will lay

03:35:50.950 --> 03:35:58.050
thy stones with fair colors and lay thy foundations with sapphires, and I will make thy windows of

03:35:58.050 --> 03:36:05.330
agates and thy gates of carbuncles and all thy borders of pleasant stones, and all thy children

03:36:05.330 --> 03:36:11.310
shall be taught of the Lord and great shall be the peace of thy children. In righteousness

03:36:11.310 --> 03:36:17.550
shalt thou be established, thou shalt be far from oppression, for thou shalt not fear,

03:36:17.850 --> 03:36:24.330
and from terror, for it shall not come near thee. Behold, they shall surely gather together,

03:36:24.470 --> 03:36:30.430
but not by me, whosoever shall gather together against thee shall fall for thy sake.

03:36:31.370 --> 03:36:37.330
Behold, I have created the smith that bloweth the coals in the fire and that bringeth forth an

03:36:37.330 --> 03:36:43.770
instrument for his work, and I have created the waster to destroy. No weapon that is formed

03:36:43.770 --> 03:36:48.830
against thee shall prosper, and every tongue that shall rise against thee in judgment,

03:36:49.250 --> 03:36:53.710
thou shalt condemn. This is the heritage of the servants of the Lord,

03:36:53.930 --> 03:36:57.310
and their righteousness is of me, saith the Lord.

03:37:50.450 --> 03:38:07.710
For that which is not bread, and your labor for that which satisfieth not. Harken diligently unto me, and eat ye that which is good, and let your soul delight itself in fatness.

03:38:07.710 --> 03:38:21.330
Incline your ear, and come unto me. Here, and your soul shall live, and I will make an everlasting covenant with you, even the sure mercies of David.

03:38:21.330 --> 03:38:48.050
Behold, I have given him for a witness to the people, a leader, and a commander to the people. Behold, thou shalt call a nation that thou knowest not, and nations that knew not thee shall run unto thee, because of the Lord thy God, and for the Holy One of Israel, for he hath glorified thee.

03:38:48.050 --> 03:39:09.190
Seek ye the Lord, while he may be found. Call ye upon him, while he is near. Let the wicked forsake his way, and the unrighteous man his thoughts, and let him return unto the Lord, and he will have mercy upon him.

03:39:09.190 --> 03:39:32.450
And to our God, for he will abundantly pardon. For my thoughts are not your thoughts, neither are your ways, my ways saith the Lord. For as the heavens are higher than the earth, so are my ways higher than your ways, and my thoughts than your thoughts.

03:39:32.450 --> 03:39:51.390
For as the rain cometh down, and the snow from heaven, and returneth not thither, but watereth the earth, and maketh it bring forth and bud, that it may give seed to the sower, and bread to the eater.

03:39:51.390 --> 03:40:10.410
So shall my word be, that goeth forth out of my mouth, it shall not return unto me void, but it shall accomplish that which I please, and it shall prosper in the thing whereto I sent it.

03:40:10.410 --> 03:40:26.150
For ye shall go out with joy, and be led forth with peace. The mountains and the hills shall break forth before you into singing, and all the trees of the field shall clap their hands.

03:40:26.150 --> 03:40:43.950
Instead of the thorn shall come up the fir tree, and instead of the briar shall come up the myrtle tree. And it shall be to the Lord for a name, for an everlasting sign, that shall not be cut off.

03:40:46.050 --> 03:40:58.970
Chapter 56 Thus saith the Lord, Keep ye judgment, and do justice, for my salvation is near to come, and my righteousness to be revealed.

03:40:58.970 --> 03:41:13.790
Blessed is the man that doeth this, and the son of man that layeth hold on it, that keepeth the Sabbath from polluting it, and keepeth his hand from doing any evil.

03:41:13.790 --> 03:41:31.190
Neither let the son of the stranger that have joined himself to the Lord speak, saying, The Lord hath utterly separated me from his people. Neither let the eunuch say, Behold, I am a dry tree.

03:41:31.190 --> 03:41:52.670
For thus saith the Lord unto the eunuchs that keep my Sabbath, and choose the things that please me, and take hold of my covenant. Even unto them will I give in mine house and within my walls a place and a name, better than of sons and of daughters.

03:41:58.790 --> 03:42:22.650
For thus saith the Lord unto the eunuchs that keep my Sabbath, and choose the things that please me, and take hold of my covenant. Even unto them will I give in mine house and within my walls a place and a name, better than of sons and of daughters.

03:42:37.250 --> 03:42:52.630
For thus saith the Lord unto the eunuchs that keep my Sabbath, and choose the things that please me, and take hold of my covenant. Even unto them will I give in mine house and within my walls a place and a name, better than of sons and of daughters.

03:42:53.970 --> 03:43:08.930
Yea, all ye beasts in the forest, his watchmen are blind, they are all ignorant, they are all dumb dogs, they cannot bark, sleeping, lying down, loving to slumber.

03:43:08.930 --> 03:43:24.290
Yea, they are greedy dogs which can never have enough, and they are shepherds that cannot understand, they all look to their own way, every one for his gain from his quarter.

03:43:24.290 --> 03:43:38.230
Come ye, say, they I will fetch wine, and we will fill ourselves with strong drink, and tomorrow shall be as this day, and much more abundant.

03:43:38.230 --> 03:43:54.990
Chapter 57. The righteous perisheth, and no man layeth to heart, and merciful men are taken away, none, considering that the righteous is taken away from the evil to come.

03:43:54.990 --> 03:44:21.090
He shall enter into peace, they shall rest in their beds, each one walking in his uprightness. But draw near hither ye sons of the sorceress, the seed of the adulterer and the whore, against whom do ye sport yourselves, against whom make ye a wide mouth and draw out the tongue.

03:44:21.090 --> 03:44:37.450
Are ye not children of transgression, a seed of falsehood, inflaming yourselves with idols, under every green tree, slaying the children in the valleys, under the cliffs of the rocks?

03:44:37.450 --> 03:44:55.530
Among the smooth stones of the stream is thy portion, they, they are thy lot, even to them hast thou poured a drink offering, thou hast offered a meat offering, should I receive comfort in these?

03:44:55.530 --> 03:45:18.070
Upon a lofty high mountain hast thou set thy bed, even thither wentest thou up to offer sacrifice. Behold, the doors also and the posts hast thou set up thy remembrance, for thou hast discovered thyself to another than me, and art gone up.

03:45:18.070 --> 03:45:42.030
Thou hast enlarged thy bed, and made thee a covenant with them, thou lovest their bed where thou sawest it, and thou wentest to the king with ointment, and didst increase thy perfumes, and didst send thy messengers far off, and didst debase thyself even unto hell.

03:45:42.030 --> 03:45:55.270
Thou art wearied in the greatness of thy way, yet, saidest thou not, there is no hope, thou hast found the life of thine hand, therefore thou wast not grieved.

03:45:55.270 --> 03:46:19.010
And of whom hast thou been afraid or feared that thou hast lied, and hast not remembered me, nor laid it to thy heart? Have not I held my peace, even of old, and thou fearest me not? I will declare thy righteousness and thy works, for they shall not profit thee.

03:46:19.010 --> 03:46:39.770
And when thou cryest, let thy companies deliver thee, but the wind shall carry them all away, vanity shall take them, but he that putteth his trust in me shall possess the land, and shall inherit my holy mountain.

03:46:39.770 --> 03:46:49.010
And shall say, Cast ye up, cast ye up, prepare the way, take up the stumbling-back out of the way of my people.

03:46:49.010 --> 03:47:12.470
For thus saith the High and Lofty One, that inhabiteth eternity, whose name is holy, I dwell in the high and holy place with him. Also that is of a contrite and humble spirit, to revive the spirit of the humble, and to revive the heart of the contrite ones.

03:47:12.470 --> 03:47:24.370
For I will not contend for ever, neither will I be always wroth, for the spirit shall fail before me, and the souls which I have made.

03:47:24.370 --> 03:47:53.750
For the iniquity of his covetousness was I wroth, and smote him. I hid me and was wroth, and he went on forwardly in the way of his heart. I have seen his way and will heal him. I will lead him also and restore comforts unto him, and to his mourners I create the fruit of the lips.

03:47:53.750 --> 03:48:17.970
Peace, peace to him that is far off, and to him that is near, saith the Lord, and I will heal him. But the wicked are like the troubled sea, when it cannot rest, whose waters cast up mire and dirt. There is no peace, saith my God to the wicked.

03:48:19.970 --> 03:48:48.930
Chapter 58 Cry aloud, spare not, lift up thy voice

03:48:48.930 --> 03:48:56.750
like a trumpet, and show my people their transgression, and the house of Jacob, their sins. Yet they

03:48:56.750 --> 03:49:03.770
seek me daily, and delight to know my ways, as a nation that did righteousness, and forsook

03:49:03.770 --> 03:49:10.410
not the ordinance of their God. They ask of me the ordinances of justice, they take delight

03:49:10.410 --> 03:49:16.610
in approaching to God. Wherefore have we fasted, say they, and thou seest not? Wherefore have

03:49:16.610 --> 03:49:22.970
we afflicted our soul, and thou takest no knowledge? Behold, in the day of your fast,

03:49:23.430 --> 03:49:31.450
ye find pleasure, and exact all your labours. Behold, ye fast for strife and debate, and

03:49:31.450 --> 03:49:38.130
to smite with the fist of wickedness. Ye shall not fast as ye do this day, to make your voice

03:49:38.130 --> 03:49:44.450
to be heard on high. Is it such a fast that I have chosen, a day for a man to afflict

03:49:44.450 --> 03:49:51.190
his soul? Is it to bow down his head as a bulrush, and to spread sackcloth and ashes

03:49:51.190 --> 03:49:58.830
under him? Wilt thou call this a fast and an acceptable day to the Lord? Is not this

03:49:58.830 --> 03:50:04.990
the fast that I have chosen, to loose the bands of wickedness, to undo the heavy burdens,

03:50:05.230 --> 03:50:12.530
and to let the oppressed go free, and that ye break every yoke? Is it not to deal thy

03:50:12.530 --> 03:50:19.010
bread to the hungry, and that thou bring the poor that are cast out to thy house, when thou seest

03:50:19.010 --> 03:50:26.110
an acre that thou cover him, and that thou hide not thyself from thine own flesh? Then shall thy

03:50:26.110 --> 03:50:32.850
light break forth as the morning, and thine health shall spring forth speedily, and thy righteousness

03:50:32.850 --> 03:50:39.990
shall go before thee. The glory of the Lord shall be thy rear reward. Then shall thou call and the

03:50:39.990 --> 03:50:47.090
Lord shall answer. Thou shall cry, and he shall say, Here I am. If thou take away from the midst

03:50:47.090 --> 03:50:54.630
of thee the yoke, the putting forth of the finger, and speaking vanity, and if thou draw out thy soul

03:50:54.630 --> 03:51:02.570
to the hungry, and satisfy the afflicted soul, then shall thy light rise in obscurity, and thy

03:51:02.570 --> 03:51:10.650
darkness be as the noonday, and the Lord shall guide thee continually, and satisfy thy soul in

03:51:10.650 --> 03:51:18.890
drought, and make fat thy bones, and thou shall be like a watered garden, and like a spring of water

03:51:18.890 --> 03:51:25.770
whose waters fail not, and they that shall be of thee shall build the old waste places.

03:51:26.330 --> 03:51:32.250
Thou shalt raise up the foundations of many generations, and thou shalt be called the

03:51:32.250 --> 03:51:40.090
repairer of the breach, the restorer of paths to dwelling. If thou turn away thy foot from the

03:51:40.090 --> 03:51:47.670
Sabbath, from doing thy pleasure on my holy day, and call the Sabbath the delight, the holy of the

03:51:47.670 --> 03:51:55.850
Lord, honorable, and shalt honor him, not doing thine own ways, nor finding thine own pleasure,

03:51:56.350 --> 03:52:04.090
nor speaking thine own words, then shalt thou delight thyself in the Lord, and I will cause

03:52:04.090 --> 03:52:11.470
thee to ride upon the high places of the earth, and feed thee with the heritage of Jacob thy father,

03:52:11.470 --> 03:52:19.190
for the mouth of the Lord hath spoken it. Chapter 59 Behold, the Lord's hand is not

03:52:19.190 --> 03:52:26.710
shortened, that it cannot save, neither his ear heavy, that it cannot hear. But your iniquities

03:52:26.710 --> 03:52:32.690
have separated between you and your God, and your sins have hid his face from you,

03:52:32.830 --> 03:52:39.970
that he will not hear. For your hands are defiled with blood, and your fingers with iniquity.

03:52:39.970 --> 03:52:47.570
Your lips have spoken lies, your tongue hath muttered perverseness. None calleth for justice,

03:52:48.030 --> 03:52:55.770
nor any pleadeth for truth. They trust in vanity, and speak lies. They conceive mischief,

03:52:55.810 --> 03:53:03.430
and bring forth iniquity. They hatch cockatrice eggs, and weave the spider's web. He that eateth

03:53:03.430 --> 03:53:10.450
their eggs dieth, and that which is crushed breaketh out into a viper. Their webs shall

03:53:10.450 --> 03:53:16.550
not become garments, neither shall they cover themselves with their works. Their works are

03:53:16.550 --> 03:53:23.130
works of iniquity, and the act of violence is in their hands. Their feet run to evil,

03:53:23.430 --> 03:53:29.470
and they make haste to shed innocent blood. Their thoughts are thoughts of iniquity.

03:53:29.470 --> 03:53:36.970
Wasting and destruction are in their paths. The way of peace they know not, and there is no

03:53:36.970 --> 03:53:44.450
judgment in their goings. They have made them crooked paths. Whosoever goeth therein shall not

03:53:44.450 --> 03:53:52.300
know peace. Therefore is judgment far from us. Neither doth justice overtake us. We wait for

03:53:52.300 --> 03:53:59.980
light, but behold obscurity, for brightness, but we walk in darkness. We grope for the wall

03:53:59.980 --> 03:54:07.800
like the blind, and we grope as if we had no eyes. We stumble at noonday as in the night.

03:54:08.320 --> 03:54:17.400
We are in desolate places as dead men. We roar all like bears, and mourn sore like doves.

03:54:17.400 --> 03:54:24.140
We look for judgment, but there is none, for salvation, but it is far off from us.

03:54:24.620 --> 03:54:31.620
For our transgressions are multiplied before thee, and our sins testify against us. For our

03:54:31.620 --> 03:54:38.200
transgressions are with us, and as for our iniquities we know them, in transgressing and

03:54:38.200 --> 03:54:45.460
lying against the Lord, and departing away from our God. Speaking oppression and revolt,

03:54:45.460 --> 03:54:52.760
conceiving and uttering from the heart words of falsehood. And judgment is turned away backward,

03:54:53.320 --> 03:55:01.380
and justice standeth afar off. For truth is fallen in the street, and equity cannot enter.

03:55:02.160 --> 03:55:10.020
Yea, truth faileth, and he that departeth from evil maketh himself a prey. And the Lord saw it,

03:55:10.020 --> 03:55:16.520
and it displeased him that there was no judgment. And he saw that there was no man, and wondered

03:55:16.520 --> 03:55:24.160
that there was no intercessor. Therefore his arm brought salvation unto him, and his righteousness

03:55:24.160 --> 03:55:32.080
it sustained him. For he put on righteousness as a breastplate, and a helmet of salvation upon his

03:55:32.080 --> 03:55:39.060
head. And he put on the garments of vengeance for clothing, and was clad with zeal as a cloak.

03:55:39.060 --> 03:55:47.340
According to their deeds, accordingly he will repay. Fury to his adversaries, recompense to

03:55:47.340 --> 03:55:54.320
his enemies. To the islands he will repay recompense. So shall they fear the name of the

03:55:54.320 --> 03:56:01.220
Lord from the west, and his glory from the rising of the sun. When the enemy shall come in like a

03:56:01.220 --> 03:56:07.080
flood, the Spirit of the Lord shall lift up a standard against him. And the Redeemer shall

03:56:07.080 --> 03:56:13.600
come to Zion, and unto them that turn from transgression in Jacob, saith the Lord.

03:56:14.180 --> 03:56:20.740
As for me, this is my covenant with them, saith the Lord. My Spirit that is upon thee,

03:56:21.160 --> 03:56:27.360
and my words which I have put in thy mouth, shall not depart out of thy mouth, nor out of the mouth

03:56:27.360 --> 03:56:34.740
of thy seed, nor out of the mouth of thy seed's seed, saith the Lord, from henceforth and for ever.

03:56:35.540 --> 03:56:45.200
Chapter 60 Arise, shine, for thy light is come, and the glory of the Lord is risen upon thee.

03:56:45.740 --> 03:56:52.700
For behold, the darkness shall cover the earth, and gross darkness the people, but the Lord shall

03:56:52.700 --> 03:57:00.380
arise upon thee, and his glory shall be seen upon thee. And the Gentiles shall come to thy light,

03:57:00.380 --> 03:57:06.880
and kings to the brightness of thy rising. Lift up thine eyes round about and see,

03:57:07.340 --> 03:57:15.080
all they gather themselves together, they come to thee. Thy sons shall come from far, and thy

03:57:15.080 --> 03:57:22.360
daughters shall be nursed at thy side. Then thou shalt see and flow together, and thine heart shall

03:57:22.360 --> 03:57:28.760
fear and be enlarged. Because the abundance of the sea shall be converted unto thee,

03:57:28.760 --> 03:57:35.920
the forces of the Gentiles shall come unto thee. The multitude of camels shall cover thee,

03:57:36.240 --> 03:57:42.980
the dromedaries of Midian and Ephar, all they from Sheba shall come. They shall bring gold and

03:57:42.980 --> 03:57:49.700
incense, and they shall show forth the praises of the Lord. All the flocks of Kedar shall be gathered

03:57:49.700 --> 03:57:55.740
together unto thee, the rams of Nebeoth shall minister unto thee. They shall come up with

03:57:55.740 --> 03:58:03.700
acceptance on mine altar, and I will glorify the house of my glory. Who are these that fly as a

03:58:03.700 --> 03:58:10.640
cloud, and as the doves to their windows? Surely the Isles shall wait for me, and the ships of

03:58:10.640 --> 03:58:18.280
Tarshish first, to bring thy sons from far, their silver and their gold with them, unto the name of

03:58:18.280 --> 03:58:26.200
the Lord thy God, and to the Holy One of Israel, because he hath glorified thee. And the sons of

03:58:26.200 --> 03:58:33.760
strangers shall build up thy walls, and their kings shall minister unto thee. For in my wrath

03:58:33.760 --> 03:58:41.160
I smote thee, but in my favor have I had mercy on thee. Therefore thy gates shall be open

03:58:41.600 --> 03:58:48.480
continually. They shall not be shut day nor night, that men may bring unto thee the forces of the

03:58:48.480 --> 03:58:54.620
Gentiles, and that their kings may be brought. For the nation and kingdom that will not serve

03:58:54.620 --> 03:59:02.200
thee shall perish, yea, those nations shall be utterly wasted. The glory of Lebanon shall

03:59:02.200 --> 03:59:10.300
come unto thee, the fir tree, the pine tree, and the box together, to beautify the place of my

03:59:10.300 --> 03:59:17.500
sanctuary, and I will make the place of my feet glorious. The sons also of them that afflicted

03:59:17.500 --> 03:59:24.340
thee shall come bending unto thee, and all they that despised thee shall bow themselves down at

03:59:24.340 --> 03:59:31.940
the soles of thy feet, and they shall call thee the city of the Lord, the Zion of the Holy One of

03:59:31.940 --> 03:59:39.640
Israel. Whereas thou hast been forsaken and hated, so that no man went through thee, I will make thee

03:59:39.640 --> 03:59:48.320
an eternal excellency, a joy of many generations. Thou shalt also suck the milk of the Gentiles,

03:59:48.540 --> 03:59:55.080
and shalt suck the breast of kings, and thou shalt know that I the Lord, and thy Savior,

03:59:55.440 --> 04:00:03.320
and thy Redeemer, the mighty one of Jacob. For brass I will bring gold, and for iron

04:00:03.320 --> 04:00:12.120
I will bring silver, and for wood brass, and for stones iron. I will also make thy officers

04:00:12.120 --> 04:00:19.580
peace, and thine exactors righteousness. Violence shall no more be heard in thy land,

04:00:20.100 --> 04:00:27.120
wasting nor destruction within thy borders, but thou shalt call thy walls salvation,

04:00:27.120 --> 04:00:35.280
and thy gates praise. The sun shall be no more thy light by day, neither for brightness

04:00:35.280 --> 04:00:41.860
shall the moon give light unto thee, but the Lord shall be unto thee an everlasting light,

04:00:42.260 --> 04:00:49.860
and thy God thy glory. Thy sun shall no more go down, neither shall thy moon withdraw itself,

04:00:50.280 --> 04:00:55.940
for the Lord shall be thy everlasting light, and the days of thy morning shall be ended.

04:00:55.940 --> 04:01:03.480
Thy people also shall be all righteous, they shall inherit the land forever, the branch of

04:01:03.480 --> 04:01:11.820
my planting, the work of my hands, that I may be glorified. A little one shall become a thousand,

04:01:12.160 --> 04:01:19.920
and a small one a strong nation. I the Lord will hasten it in his time.

04:01:26.480 --> 04:01:27.180
you

04:01:39.700 --> 04:01:40.340
CHAPTER 61.

04:01:52.420 --> 04:01:59.060
The Spirit of the Lord God is upon me, because the Lord hath anointed me to preach good

04:01:59.060 --> 04:02:06.020
tidings unto the meek. He hath sent me to bind up the brokenhearted, to proclaim liberty

04:02:06.020 --> 04:02:13.220
to the captives, and the opening of the prison to them that are bound, to proclaim the acceptable

04:02:13.220 --> 04:02:20.800
year of the Lord, and the day of vengeance of our God, to comfort all that mourn, to

04:02:20.800 --> 04:02:28.380
appoint unto them that mourn in Zion, to give unto them beauty for ashes, the oil of joy

04:02:28.380 --> 04:02:35.700
for mourning, the garment of praise for the spirit of heaviness, that they might be called

04:02:35.700 --> 04:02:43.520
trees of righteousness, the planting of the Lord, that he might be glorified. And they

04:02:43.520 --> 04:02:50.740
shall build the old wastes, they shall raise up the former desolations, and they shall

04:02:50.740 --> 04:02:58.260
repair the waste cities, the desolations of many generations. And strangers shall stand

04:02:58.260 --> 04:03:05.820
and feed your flocks, and the sons of the alien shall be your plowmen and your vinedressers.

04:03:07.040 --> 04:03:14.120
But ye shall be named the priests of the Lord, men shall call you the ministers of our God,

04:03:14.660 --> 04:03:21.060
ye shall eat the riches of the Gentiles, and in their glory shall ye boast yourselves.

04:03:22.080 --> 04:03:29.880
For your shame ye shall have double, and for confusion they shall rejoice in their portion,

04:03:30.180 --> 04:03:36.520
therefore in their land they shall possess the double, everlasting joy shall be unto them.

04:03:37.740 --> 04:03:44.860
For I the Lord love judgment, I hate robbery for burnt offering, and I will direct their work in

04:03:44.860 --> 04:03:51.320
truth, and I will make an everlasting covenant with them. And their seed shall be known among

04:03:51.320 --> 04:03:58.070
the Gentiles, and their offspring among the people. All that see them shall acknowledge them,

04:03:58.920 --> 04:04:05.300
that they are the seed which the Lord hath blessed. I will greatly rejoice in the Lord,

04:04:05.340 --> 04:04:11.610
my soul shall be joyful in my God, for he hath clothed me with the garments of salvation,

04:04:11.610 --> 04:04:18.210
he hath covered me with the robe of righteousness, and as a bridegroom decketh himself with

04:04:18.210 --> 04:04:26.110
ornaments, and as a bride adorneth herself with her jewels. For as the earth bringeth forth her

04:04:26.110 --> 04:04:34.290
bud, and as the garden causeth the things that are sown in it to spring forth, so the Lord God

04:04:34.290 --> 04:04:40.650
will cause righteousness and praise to spring forth before all the nations.

04:04:41.530 --> 04:04:51.230
Chapter 62 For Zion's sake will I not hold my peace, and for Jerusalem's sake I will not rest,

04:04:51.730 --> 04:04:58.810
until the righteousness thereof go forth as brightness, and the salvation thereof as a lamp

04:05:00.170 --> 04:05:07.790
And the Gentiles shall see thy righteousness, and all kings thy glory, and thou shalt be

04:05:07.790 --> 04:05:14.830
called by a new name, which the mouth of the Lord shall name. Thou shalt also be a crown of

04:05:14.830 --> 04:05:23.230
glory in the hand of the Lord, and a royal diadem in the hand of thy God. Thou shalt no more be

04:05:23.230 --> 04:05:32.110
termed forsaken, neither shall thy land any more be termed desolate. But thou shalt be called

04:05:32.770 --> 04:05:43.030
Hepsava, and thy land Beulah, for the Lord delighteth in thee, and thy land shall be married. For as a

04:05:43.030 --> 04:05:50.790
young man marryeth a virgin, so shall thy sons marry thee, and as the bridegroom rejoiceth over

04:05:50.790 --> 04:05:58.690
the bride, so shall thy God rejoice over thee. I have set watchmen upon thy walls, O Jerusalem,

04:05:59.210 --> 04:06:07.350
which shall never hold their peace day nor night. Ye that make mention of the Lord keep not silence,

04:06:08.190 --> 04:06:14.190
and give him no rest till he establish, and till he make Jerusalem a praise in the earth.

04:06:15.270 --> 04:06:22.390
The Lord hath sworn by his right hand, and by the arm of his strength, surely I will no more give

04:06:22.390 --> 04:06:30.130
thy corn to be meat for thine enemies, and the sons of the stranger shall not drink thy wine,

04:06:30.190 --> 04:06:38.410
for which thou hast laboured. But they that have gathered it shall eat it, and praise the Lord,

04:06:38.410 --> 04:06:44.190
and they that have brought it together shall drink it in the courts of my holiness.

04:06:46.290 --> 04:06:53.450
Go through, go through the gates, prepare ye the way of the people. Cast up, cast up the highway,

04:06:53.910 --> 04:07:01.290
gather out the stones, lift up a standard for the people. Behold, the Lord hath proclaimed unto the

04:07:01.290 --> 04:07:08.490
end of the world, say ye to the daughter of Zion, Behold, thy salvation cometh. Behold,

04:07:08.910 --> 04:07:16.890
his reward is with him, and his work before him. And they shall call them the holy people,

04:07:17.590 --> 04:07:24.870
the redeemed of the Lord, and thou shalt be called sought out, a city not forsaken.

04:07:25.870 --> 04:07:35.230
Chapter 63 Who is this that cometh from Edom, with dyed garments from Bosra? This that is

04:07:35.230 --> 04:07:41.450
glorious in his apparel, travelling in the greatness of his strength, I that speak in

04:07:41.450 --> 04:07:49.290
righteousness, mighty to save. Wherefore art thou red in thine apparel, and thy garments like him

04:07:49.290 --> 04:07:56.290
that treadeth in the wine-fat? I have trodden the wine-press alone, and of the people there

04:07:56.290 --> 04:08:04.530
was none with me. For I will tread them in mine anger, and trample them in my fury, and their

04:08:04.530 --> 04:08:15.570
blood shall be sprinkled upon my garments. And I will stain all my reinment, for the day of

04:08:15.570 --> 04:08:23.870
his coming. And I looked, and there was none to help, and I wondered that there was none to uphold.

04:08:24.630 --> 04:08:30.930
Therefore mine own arm brought salvation unto me, and my fury it upheld me.

04:08:32.750 --> 04:08:39.770
And I will tread down the people in mine anger, and make them drunk in my fury, and I will bring

04:08:39.770 --> 04:08:46.010
their strength down to the earth. I will mention the loving kindness of the Lord,

04:08:46.710 --> 04:08:51.390
and the praises of the Lord according to all that the Lord hath bestowed on us,

04:08:52.670 --> 04:08:58.370
and the great goodness toward the house of Israel, which he hath bestowed on them according to his

04:08:58.370 --> 04:09:07.050
mercies, and according to the multitude of his loving kindness. For he said, surely they are

04:09:07.050 --> 04:09:16.150
my people, children that will not lie. So he was their Saviour. In all their affliction

04:09:16.150 --> 04:09:24.210
he was afflicted, and the angel of his presence saved them. In his love and in his pity he redeemed

04:09:24.210 --> 04:09:36.350
them, and he bare them, and carried them all the days of old. But they rebelled, and vexed his

04:09:36.350 --> 04:09:44.670
enemy, and he fought against them. Then he remembered the days of old, Moses and his people,

04:09:44.770 --> 04:09:50.850
saying, Where is he that brought them up out of the sea with the shepherd of his flock?

04:09:51.470 --> 04:09:57.730
Where is he that put his Holy Spirit within him, that led them by the right hand of Moses

04:09:57.730 --> 04:10:05.450
with his glorious arm, dividing the water before them, to make himself an everlasting name?

04:10:06.350 --> 04:10:13.050
That led them through the deep, as an horse in the wilderness, that they should not stumble.

04:10:13.810 --> 04:10:20.650
As the beast goeth down into the valley, the Spirit of the Lord caused him to rest. So didst

04:10:20.650 --> 04:10:36.330
thou lead thy people, to make thyself a glorious name. Look down from heaven, and behold from the

04:10:37.050 --> 04:10:44.830
sounding of thy bowels and of thy mercies toward me. Are they restrained? Doubtless thou art our

04:10:44.830 --> 04:10:52.770
Father, though Abraham be ignorant of us, and Israel acknowledges not, thou, O Lord, art our

04:10:52.770 --> 04:11:02.090
Father, our Redeemer, thy name is from everlasting. O Lord, why hast thou made us to err from thy ways,

04:11:02.090 --> 04:11:10.230
and harden our heart from thy fear? Return for thy servant's sake, the tribes of thine inheritance.

04:11:11.370 --> 04:11:18.510
The people of thy holiness have possessed it but a little while. Our adversaries have trodden down

04:11:18.510 --> 04:11:27.090
thy sanctuary. We are thine. Thou never bearest rule over them. They were not called by thy name.

04:11:32.090 --> 04:11:33.050
Michael Packard

04:11:41.630 --> 04:12:04.030
64. O, that thou wouldst rend the heavens, that thou wouldst come down, that the mountains

04:12:04.030 --> 04:12:11.170
might flow down at thy presence, as when the melting fire burneth, the fire causeth the

04:12:11.170 --> 04:12:17.810
waters to boil, to make thy name known to thine adversaries, that the nations may tremble

04:12:17.810 --> 04:12:25.270
at thy presence. When thou didst terrible things, which we looked not for, thou camest

04:12:25.270 --> 04:12:32.830
down, the mountains flowed down at thy presence. For since the beginning of the world men have

04:12:32.830 --> 04:12:40.710
not heard, nor perceived by the ear, neither hath the eye seen, O God, beside thee, what he hath

04:12:40.710 --> 04:12:47.790
prepared for him that waiteth for him. Thou meetest him that rejoiceth, and worketh righteousness,

04:12:48.510 --> 04:12:57.070
those that remember thee in thy ways. Behold, thou art wroth, for we have sinned in those in

04:12:57.070 --> 04:13:06.670
and we shall be saved. But we are all as an unclean thing, and all our righteousness are

04:13:06.670 --> 04:13:15.370
as filthy rags, and we all do fade as a leaf, and our iniquities, like the wind, have taken us away.

04:13:16.090 --> 04:13:22.070
And there is none that calleth upon thy name, that stirreth up himself to take hold of thee,

04:13:22.070 --> 04:13:30.030
for thou hast hid thy face from us, and hast consumed us, because of our iniquities. But now,

04:13:30.090 --> 04:13:38.730
O Lord, thou art our Father, we are the clay, and thou our potter, and we all are the work of thy

04:13:38.730 --> 04:13:46.270
hand. Be not wroth very sore, O Lord, neither remember iniquity forever. Behold, see, we

04:13:47.270 --> 04:13:57.290
are thy people, thy holy cities are a wilderness, Zion is a wilderness, Jerusalem a desolation.

04:13:58.190 --> 04:14:04.600
Our holy and our beautiful house, where our fathers praised thee, is burned up with fire,

04:14:05.630 --> 04:14:11.950
and all our pleasant things are laid waste. Wilt thou refrain thyself for these things,

04:14:11.950 --> 04:14:16.570
O Lord? Wilt thou hold thy peace and afflict us very sore?

04:14:17.610 --> 04:14:26.690
Chapter 65. I am sought of them that ask not for me. I am found of them that sought me not.

04:14:27.310 --> 04:14:36.830
I said, Behold me, behold me unto a nation that was not called by my name. I have spread out my

04:14:36.830 --> 04:14:44.290
hands all the day unto a rebellious people, which walketh in a way that was not good after

04:14:44.290 --> 04:14:53.450
their own thoughts. A people that provoketh me to anger continually to my face, that sacrificeth

04:14:53.450 --> 04:15:01.630
in gardens, and burneth incense upon altars of brick, which remain among the graves, and lodge

04:15:01.630 --> 04:15:09.550
in the monuments, which eat swine's flesh, and broth of abominable things is in their vessels,

04:15:10.250 --> 04:15:19.170
which say, Stand by thyself, come not near to me, for I am holier than thou. These are a smoke in

04:15:19.170 --> 04:15:29.750
my nose, a fire that burneth all the day. Behold, it is written before me, I will not keep silence,

04:15:29.750 --> 04:15:38.850
but will recompense, even recompense into their bosom, your iniquities, and the iniquities of

04:15:38.850 --> 04:15:46.270
your fathers together, saith the Lord, which have burned incense upon the mountains, and blasphemed

04:15:46.270 --> 04:15:54.250
me upon the hills. Therefore will I measure their former work into their bosom, thus saith the Lord,

04:15:54.810 --> 04:16:03.270
as the new wine is found in the cluster, and one saith, Destroy it not, for a blessing is in it.

04:16:04.510 --> 04:16:13.210
So will I do for my servant's sake, that I may not destroy them all. And I will bring forth a

04:16:13.210 --> 04:16:21.210
seed out of Jacob, and out of Judah, an inheritor of my mountains, and mine elect shall inherit it,

04:16:21.210 --> 04:16:29.830
and my servant shall dwell there. And Sharon shall be a fold of flocks, and the valley of Acre,

04:16:30.430 --> 04:16:37.910
a place for the herds to lie down in, for my people that have sought me. But ye are they that

04:16:37.910 --> 04:16:44.650
forsake the Lord, that forget my holy mountain, that prepare a table for that troop, and that

04:16:44.650 --> 04:16:50.510
furnish the drink offering unto that number. Therefore will I number you to the sword, and

04:16:50.510 --> 04:16:58.230
ye shall all bow down to the slaughter. Because when I called, ye did not answer. When I spake,

04:16:58.450 --> 04:17:06.390
ye did not hear, but did evil before mine eyes, and did choose that wherein I delighted not.

04:17:07.410 --> 04:17:14.310
Therefore thus saith the Lord God, Behold, my servants shall eat, but ye shall be hungry.

04:17:14.310 --> 04:17:22.110
Behold, my servants shall drink, but ye shall be thirsty. Behold, my servants shall rejoice,

04:17:23.310 --> 04:17:32.450
but ye shall be ashamed. Behold, my servants shall sing for joy of heart, but ye shall cry for sorrow

04:17:32.450 --> 04:17:40.830
of heart, and shall howl for vexation of spirit. And ye shall leave your name for a curse unto my

04:17:40.830 --> 04:17:49.710
chosen, for the Lord God shall slay thee, and call his servants by another name. That he who

04:17:49.710 --> 04:17:56.250
blesseth himself in the earth shall bless himself in the God of truth, and he that sweareth in the

04:17:56.250 --> 04:18:03.510
earth shall swear by the God of truth, because the former troubles are forgotten, and because

04:18:03.510 --> 04:18:12.050
they are hid from mine eyes. For behold, I create new heavens and a new earth, and the former shall

04:18:12.050 --> 04:18:20.750
not be remembered, nor come into mind. But be ye glad and rejoice forever in that which I create.

04:18:21.310 --> 04:18:30.110
For behold, I create Jerusalem a rejoicing, and her people a joy, and I will rejoice in Jerusalem,

04:18:30.110 --> 04:18:38.050
and joy in my people. And the voice of weeping shall be no more heard in her, nor the voice of

04:18:38.050 --> 04:18:45.830
crying. There shall be no more thence an infant of days, nor an old man that hath not filled his

04:18:45.830 --> 04:18:52.710
days. For the child shall die and hundred years old, but the sinner being and hundred years old

04:18:52.710 --> 04:18:59.850
shall be accursed. And they shall build their houses and inhabit them, and they shall plant

04:18:59.850 --> 04:19:07.230
vineyards and eat the fruit of them. They shall not build and another inhabit, they shall not plant

04:19:07.230 --> 04:19:15.190
and another eat. For as the days of a tree are the days of my people, and mine elect shall long enjoy

04:19:15.190 --> 04:19:23.110
the work of their hands. They shall not labor in vain, nor bring forth for trouble. For they are

04:19:23.110 --> 04:19:29.350
the seed of the blessed of the Lord, and their offspring with them. And it shall come to pass,

04:19:30.150 --> 04:19:39.230
that before they call I will answer, and while they are yet speaking I will hear. The wolf and

04:19:39.230 --> 04:19:47.430
shall feed together, and the lion shall eat straw like the bullock, and dust shall be the serpent's

04:19:47.430 --> 04:19:55.150
meat. They shall not hurt nor destroy in all my holy mountains, saith the Lord. Chapter 66

04:19:55.790 --> 04:20:06.530
Thus saith the Lord, The heaven is my throne, and the earth is my footstool. Where is the

04:20:06.530 --> 04:20:15.630
place of my rest? For all those things hath mine hand made, and all those things have been, saith

04:20:15.630 --> 04:20:23.510
the Lord. But to this man I will look, even to him that is poor, and of a contrite spirit,

04:20:24.130 --> 04:20:33.950
and trembleth at my word. He that killeth an ox is as if he slew a man. He that sacrificeth a lamb

04:20:33.950 --> 04:20:42.250
is as if he cut off a dog's neck. He that offereth an oblation is as if he offered swine's blood.

04:20:42.810 --> 04:20:49.550
He that burneth incense is as if he blessed an idol. Yea, they have chosen their own ways,

04:20:50.770 --> 04:20:56.470
and their soul delighteth in their abominations. I also will choose their delusions,

04:20:56.810 --> 04:21:03.510
and will bring their fears upon them, because when I called none did answer. When I spake

04:21:03.510 --> 04:21:11.270
they did not hear, but they did evil before mine eyes, and chose that in which I delighted not.

04:21:12.770 --> 04:21:19.490
Hear the word of the Lord, ye that tremble at his word, your brethren that hated you, that cast you

04:21:19.490 --> 04:21:26.750
out for my name's sake, said, Let the Lord be glorified. But he shall appear to your joy,

04:21:26.750 --> 04:21:35.030
and they shall be ashamed. A voice of noise from the city, a voice from the temple,

04:21:35.470 --> 04:21:42.510
a voice of the Lord that rendereth recompense to his enemies. Before she travailed, she brought

04:21:42.510 --> 04:21:49.750
forth, before her pain came she was delivered of a man-child. Who hath heard such a thing?

04:21:50.610 --> 04:21:57.090
Who hath seen such things? Shall the earth be made to bring forth in one day,

04:21:58.170 --> 04:22:06.550
or shall a nation be born at once? For as soon as Zion travailed, she brought forth her children.

04:22:07.490 --> 04:22:13.990
Shall I bring to the birth, and not cause to bring forth, saith the Lord? Shall I cause to bring

04:22:13.990 --> 04:22:20.670
and shut the womb, saith thy God? Rejoice ye with Jerusalem, and be glad with her.

04:22:21.070 --> 04:22:26.950
All ye that love her, rejoice for joy with her. All ye that mourn for her,

04:22:28.510 --> 04:22:33.530
that ye may suck and be satisfied with the breasts of her consolations,

04:22:34.170 --> 04:22:39.370
that ye may milk out and be delighted with the abundance of her glory.

04:22:40.430 --> 04:22:46.050
For thus saith the Lord, Behold, I will extend peace to her like a river,

04:22:46.530 --> 04:22:55.790
and the glory of the Gentiles like a flowing stream. Then shall ye suck, ye shall be born upon

04:22:55.790 --> 04:23:05.690
her sides, and be dandled upon her knees. As one whom his mother comforteth, so I will comfort you,

04:23:05.690 --> 04:23:13.690
and ye shall be comforted in Jerusalem. And when ye see this, your heart shall rejoice,

04:23:14.010 --> 04:23:19.890
and your bones shall flourish like an herb, and the hand of the Lord shall be known

04:23:19.890 --> 04:23:27.970
toward his servants, and his indignation toward his enemies. For behold, the Lord will come with

04:23:27.970 --> 04:23:35.350
fire, and with his chariots like a whirlwind, to render his anger with fury, and his rebuke

04:23:35.350 --> 04:23:42.210
with flames of fire. For by fire and by his sword will the Lord plead with all flesh,

04:23:43.150 --> 04:23:50.410
and the slain of the Lord shall be many. They that sanctify themselves, and purify themselves

04:23:50.410 --> 04:23:56.750
in the gardens behind one tree in the midst, eating swine's flesh, and the abomination,

04:23:57.150 --> 04:24:03.050
and the mouse, shall be consumed together, saith the Lord. For I know their works,

04:24:03.050 --> 04:24:08.290
and their thoughts. It shall come that I will gather all nations in tongues,

04:24:08.810 --> 04:24:16.710
and they shall come and see my glory. And I will set a sign among them, and I will send those that

04:24:16.710 --> 04:24:26.430
escape of them unto the nations, to Tarshish, Pole, and Ludd, that draw the bow, to Tubal,

04:24:26.430 --> 04:24:35.090
and Javin, to the Isles afar off, that they have not heard my fame, neither have seen my glory,

04:24:35.750 --> 04:24:42.890
and they shall declare my glory among the Gentiles. And they shall bring all your brethren

04:24:42.890 --> 04:24:49.870
for an offering unto the Lord, out of all nations upon horses, and in chariots, and in litters,

04:24:49.870 --> 04:24:56.730
and upon mules, and upon swift beasts, to my holy mountain Jerusalem, saith the Lord.

04:24:57.670 --> 04:25:03.350
As the children of Israel bring an offering in a clean vessel, into the house of the Lord.

04:25:04.050 --> 04:25:10.930
And I will also take them for priests, and for Levites, saith the Lord. For as the new heavens,

04:25:11.350 --> 04:25:15.750
and the new worth which I will make, shall remain before me, saith the Lord,

04:25:15.750 --> 04:25:23.490
so shall your seed and your name remain, and it shall come to pass, that from one new moon to

04:25:23.490 --> 04:25:30.450
another, and from one Sabbath to another, shall all flesh come to worship before me, saith the Lord.

04:25:31.610 --> 04:25:37.010
And they shall go forth, and look upon the carcasses of the men that have transgressed

04:25:37.010 --> 04:25:43.830
against me, for their worm shall not die, neither shall their fire be quenched,

04:25:43.830 --> 04:25:47.630
and they shall be an abhorring unto all flesh.
